WEBVTT

00:15.515 --> 00:17.517
[bongos drumming]

00:36.870 --> 00:40.165
[flute playing]

00:50.508 --> 00:51.968
[lively music playing]

01:00.018 --> 01:01.478
Asere, ¿qué bolá?

01:01.561 --> 01:04.606
Croquetas frescas!

01:18.995 --> 01:20.705
[indistinct chatter]

01:33.426 --> 01:35.386
[street organ plays]

01:37.430 --> 01:39.057
Are you ready, Vivo?

01:39.182 --> 01:40.100
[Vivo chitters]

01:40.183 --> 01:42.769
Okay. Let's get to work.

01:42.852 --> 01:48.942
♪ Hey, ladies and gentlemen
The show is right this way ♪

01:49.025 --> 01:51.528
♪ Right this way ♪

01:52.278 --> 01:58.368
♪ Hey, we have prepared for you
A dazzling display ♪

01:58.451 --> 02:01.246
♪ Right this way ♪

02:01.871 --> 02:06.000
♪ So gather 'round, my friends
And here we go ♪

02:06.084 --> 02:12.632
♪ Presenting the one and only Vivo! ♪

02:25.645 --> 02:27.188
Is this thing on?

02:27.272 --> 02:30.483
Gather 'round. Gather 'round. Let's go!

02:30.567 --> 02:31.526
[blows nose]

02:32.318 --> 02:34.654
♪ Okay, attendance is low
But this is just a hiccup ♪

02:34.737 --> 02:37.323
♪ Once we begin our show
Business is gonna pick up ♪

02:37.407 --> 02:39.450
♪ We're two blocks from la casa
It's not a new scene ♪

02:39.576 --> 02:41.786
♪ This is our spot in the plaza
Check out the routine ♪

02:41.870 --> 02:44.038
♪ Ladies and gentlemen
I am Vivo the kinkajou ♪

02:44.122 --> 02:45.081
♪ What's a kinkajou? ♪

02:45.165 --> 02:47.208
♪ Baby, I think you're ready
To learn a thing or two ♪

02:47.292 --> 02:50.044
♪ Watch me swing as I sing at you
Every single thing I can think of ♪

02:50.128 --> 02:52.755
-♪ To make you scream, whoo! ♪
-♪ Hey ♪

02:52.839 --> 02:57.135
♪ Lo le lo lai
Lo le lo lai, lo le lo lei ♪

02:57.218 --> 03:00.430
-♪ Lai le lo lei ♪
-That's Andrés. He sings…

03:00.513 --> 03:02.056
[both] ♪ Hey ♪

03:02.140 --> 03:06.561
♪ Lo le lo lai
Lo le lo lai, lo le lo lei ♪

03:06.644 --> 03:09.397
♪ Lai le lo lei ♪

03:09.939 --> 03:14.569
♪ You and I, we are one of a kind ♪

03:14.652 --> 03:18.823
♪ Keeping time, every time ♪

03:18.907 --> 03:21.409
♪ Oye! We are a part
Of a time-honored tradition ♪

03:21.492 --> 03:24.412
♪ Of timing and precision
Your finest two musicians are top-notch ♪

03:24.495 --> 03:27.248
♪ As we hopscotch the competition
The clock is tocking and ticking ♪

03:27.332 --> 03:29.167
♪ I'm rocking this clave rhythm
Now watch ♪

03:29.250 --> 03:32.503
♪ As people drop their dollars and pesos
We do this all day ♪

03:32.587 --> 03:34.631
♪ Every day, so dame un beso ♪

03:34.714 --> 03:36.299
♪ Give me a kiss, mwah! ♪

03:36.382 --> 03:38.176
♪ Be right back
Now watch this ♪

03:38.259 --> 03:39.844
♪ Hey ♪

03:39.928 --> 03:44.224
♪ Lo le lo lai
Lo le lo lai, lo le lo lei ♪

03:44.307 --> 03:46.935
♪ Lai le lo lei ♪

03:47.602 --> 03:52.190
♪ You and I, we are one of a kind ♪

03:52.273 --> 03:56.611
♪ Keeping time, every time ♪

03:56.694 --> 03:57.862
♪ Okay, you may be thinking ♪

03:57.946 --> 03:59.948
♪ "What's a kinkajou doing
Playing music in Cuba?" ♪

04:00.031 --> 04:01.908
♪ "Don't you usually live
In the rain forest?" ♪

04:01.991 --> 04:03.785
♪ Maybe I fell
In a shipping crate as a baby ♪

04:03.868 --> 04:06.746
♪ Next thing I knew, I was somewhere new
I wasn't singing the same chorus ♪

04:06.829 --> 04:09.999
♪ All I remember was being hungry
And running from somebody even hungrier ♪

04:10.083 --> 04:11.459
♪ Chasing me up this very tree ♪

04:11.542 --> 04:13.503
♪ But guess who came
To the rescue with his tres? ♪

04:13.586 --> 04:16.256
♪ Andrés, yes
And he blessed me with his melody ♪

04:16.339 --> 04:19.133
[plucking guitar]

04:19.217 --> 04:21.010
Where did you come from, chiquito?

04:21.094 --> 04:23.012
-[Vivo chitters]
-[Andrés chuckles]

04:23.096 --> 04:25.723
Ah! You really love music, don't you?

04:26.432 --> 04:28.226
♪ Come down from the tree ♪

04:28.768 --> 04:30.687
♪ You can stay with me ♪

04:30.770 --> 04:33.314
♪ Mmm, but what will your name be? ♪

04:33.398 --> 04:34.565
[Vivo chitters]

04:34.649 --> 04:39.696
You're so full of music and life,
and I have the perfect name for you.

04:39.779 --> 04:41.823
♪ Vivo! ♪

04:41.906 --> 04:44.200
♪ And if y'all like that
Won't you pass the hat? ♪

04:44.284 --> 04:46.577
♪ Right along like that
Won't you pass the hat? ♪

04:46.661 --> 04:48.830
♪ Yeah, if y'all like that
Won't you pass the hat? ♪

04:48.913 --> 04:51.249
♪ It's Vivo
I'm faster than your average cat ♪

04:51.332 --> 04:53.584
♪ And if y'all like that
Won't you pass the hat? ♪

04:53.668 --> 04:55.920
♪ Right along like that
Won't you pass the hat? ♪

04:56.004 --> 04:58.423
♪ Yeah, if y'all like that
Won't you pass the hat? ♪

04:58.506 --> 05:00.967
♪ Yeah, I've adapted to my habitat ♪

05:01.050 --> 05:05.221
♪ You and I, we are one of a kind ♪

05:05.722 --> 05:08.057
-♪ Keeping time ♪
-♪ Keeping time ♪

05:08.141 --> 05:11.561
-♪ Right on time ♪
-♪ Right on time ♪

05:11.644 --> 05:13.187
♪ Hey! ♪

05:13.271 --> 05:16.190
♪ Lo le lo lai
Lo le lo lai, lo le lo lei ♪

05:16.274 --> 05:18.443
[crowd] ♪ We all like that
So we pass the hat ♪

05:18.526 --> 05:20.945
♪ Right along like that
So we pass the hat ♪

05:21.029 --> 05:25.658
-♪ You and I, we are one of a kind ♪
-[crowd] ♪ They are one of a kind ♪

05:25.742 --> 05:30.371
♪ Keeping time, every time ♪

05:30.455 --> 05:35.043
♪ Right on time ♪

05:35.126 --> 05:37.879
♪ Lai lo lei lo lai
Lo lei lo le lo le lai ♪

05:37.962 --> 05:39.589
-♪ Lo lai ♪
-♪ Right on time! ♪

05:39.672 --> 05:41.966
[crowd cheers]

05:42.050 --> 05:45.053
[Vivo] And that, friends,
is how you do it in Havana, Cuba.

05:45.136 --> 05:47.972
Precision, timing,
not a moment out of place.

05:48.056 --> 05:51.309
Because even though Andrés and I
might not have spoken the same language,

05:51.392 --> 05:54.645
when it came to music,
we became so in sync that, well,

05:54.729 --> 05:57.273
we finished each other's musical phrases.

05:57.357 --> 05:59.108
Ooh! [chuckles]

05:59.192 --> 06:02.195
Good show as usual, Vivo. Are you hungry?

06:02.278 --> 06:04.405
-[chirps]
-Do you want a croqueta?

06:04.489 --> 06:06.157
-[chirps]
-Maybe mangoes?

06:06.240 --> 06:07.241
Ooh!

06:07.325 --> 06:09.077
[Andrés laughs]

06:09.160 --> 06:11.245
Somebody likes mangoes.

06:11.329 --> 06:13.664
[lively music playing]

06:16.084 --> 06:19.462
[Vivo] You might look at us and think,
"Those guys got a perfect life."

06:19.545 --> 06:20.880
And you'd be right.

06:20.963 --> 06:24.050
That is… until the letter came.

06:24.133 --> 06:27.011
-¡Oiga! Señor Andrés.
-[car horn beeps]

06:27.095 --> 06:30.306
[arguing in Spanish]

06:30.390 --> 06:33.309
[arguing continues]

06:33.935 --> 06:37.355
[men exchanging pleasantries]

06:37.438 --> 06:38.439
Okay.

06:38.940 --> 06:39.899
Hoo. [sighs]

06:40.858 --> 06:43.319
[chuckles] You… [panting]

06:43.403 --> 06:44.404
…have a letter.

06:44.487 --> 06:45.988
Muchas gracias, Montoya.

06:46.072 --> 06:47.156
[sighs]

06:47.865 --> 06:48.908
-Hmm…
-[chitters]

06:51.077 --> 06:52.745
-[Vivo giggles]
-[Andrés chuckles]

06:55.415 --> 06:56.874
[gasps] Marta?

06:57.375 --> 06:58.334
[chitters]

06:58.418 --> 06:59.877
But how?

07:00.378 --> 07:02.380
Marta? Who's Marta?

07:05.591 --> 07:07.218
"Mi amor, Andrés…"

07:07.301 --> 07:09.637
"Mi amor"? Who's Marta?

07:09.720 --> 07:15.268
"What words can I write in a letter
after being separated for so many years?"

07:15.810 --> 07:19.730
[Marta] "As I prepare for retirement,
I have been flooded with memories

07:19.814 --> 07:23.109
of the beautiful music
we once made together."

07:23.192 --> 07:25.528
"I don't know
if you can forgive my silence

07:25.611 --> 07:28.156
since we separated all those years ago."

07:28.239 --> 07:32.952
"But nothing would mean more to me
than for us to sing together again."

07:33.453 --> 07:39.250
"My farewell concert is June 16th
at the Mambo Cabana in Miami."

07:39.333 --> 07:40.585
[Vivo chitters]

07:40.668 --> 07:44.714
[Andrés] "If you are there with your tres,
I'll know you feel the same."

07:46.090 --> 07:51.345
"I hope it's not too late. Amor, Marta."

07:52.472 --> 07:56.058
I can't believe it. Marta Sandoval!

07:56.142 --> 07:59.604
-Did you say Marta Sandoval?
-Marta's final show?

07:59.687 --> 08:02.523
-Hold up, hold up, hold up. Who's Marta?
-[man] You're going to Miami?

08:02.607 --> 08:05.276
No, no, no, no.
We go from the apartment to the plaza.

08:05.359 --> 08:06.986
That's our commute, two blocks.

08:07.069 --> 08:08.779
[woman] You have to go, Andrés.

08:08.863 --> 08:11.491
You can finally perform in Miami together.

08:11.574 --> 08:14.494
What? No! This is where our audience is.

08:14.577 --> 08:18.623
-I cannot go to Miami. I'm an old man.
-Yeah, great point. Know your limits.

08:18.706 --> 08:20.791
Come on, everyone.
Chip in. ¡Suelta el billete!

08:20.875 --> 08:22.210
[chitters]

08:22.293 --> 08:25.087
Andrés y Marta. Qué romántico.

08:25.171 --> 08:26.839
Uh, let's not get carried away.

08:26.923 --> 08:28.508
-[indistinct chatter]
-Who's Marta?

08:29.759 --> 08:30.968
Hello?

08:33.846 --> 08:35.890
Hey! Who is Marta?

08:39.685 --> 08:41.062
[Andrés] Mmm.

08:41.687 --> 08:43.272
[grunting]

08:46.901 --> 08:48.361
-[blowing]
-[gags]

08:49.237 --> 08:51.155
-Ay…
-[sneezes]

08:52.156 --> 08:55.576
[Vivo] Oh. Wait. This is you?

08:56.911 --> 08:59.163
I assumed you were always an old man.

09:02.458 --> 09:04.502
So you guys were like a duo?

09:05.002 --> 09:06.879
[Andrés] Marta, ay.

09:06.963 --> 09:09.090
She was the toast of Havana.

09:09.173 --> 09:12.176
She had the most beautiful voice
in all Cuba.

09:12.802 --> 09:16.264
And, uh, she was also the love of my life.

09:17.098 --> 09:19.058
But I never told her how I felt.

09:20.851 --> 09:24.313
Everybody knew
that she would be a big star someday.

09:26.190 --> 09:29.735
♪ Mi canción ♪

09:31.279 --> 09:32.613
[crowd applauds]

09:33.281 --> 09:35.658
[Andrés] One night,
after another sold-out show,

09:35.741 --> 09:37.451
I knew that this was my moment.

09:37.952 --> 09:41.581
I had finally found the courage
to tell her how I felt.

09:43.958 --> 09:48.546
But just then, we were interrupted
by a promoter from the United States.

09:48.629 --> 09:54.343
He offered Marta a chance to perform
at the Mambo Cabana in Miami.

09:54.427 --> 09:56.470
Marta was floating on air.

09:56.554 --> 09:59.432
[chuckles]
Her dream was finally coming true.

10:00.558 --> 10:02.935
And, uh, at that moment,

10:03.477 --> 10:06.689
I realized that if I told her
what was in my heart,

10:07.440 --> 10:09.817
she might not follow her heart.

10:11.277 --> 10:13.571
So, I kept my feelings to myself

10:14.655 --> 10:16.490
and said nothing.

10:17.158 --> 10:19.160
[wistful music playing]

10:27.877 --> 10:29.211
[inaudible dialogue]

10:42.141 --> 10:44.644
[Andrés] Without her, Havana was empty.

10:45.269 --> 10:46.479
I was too.

10:47.104 --> 10:50.316
All my love, all my sadness,

10:50.399 --> 10:51.859
I put it into a song.

10:51.942 --> 10:53.944
[guitar playing]

10:56.113 --> 10:59.283
It was a song too painful to play.

10:59.867 --> 11:00.743
A song

11:01.786 --> 11:03.496
Marta would never hear.

11:09.251 --> 11:10.961
Here it is, Vivo.

11:11.045 --> 11:13.172
The last song I ever wrote.

11:13.839 --> 11:17.593
[vocalizes melody]

11:17.677 --> 11:20.179
Wow. She never got to hear it.

11:21.055 --> 11:22.390
That's so sad.

11:22.973 --> 11:26.602
But now, my friend,
I have the greatest gift in the world.

11:26.686 --> 11:28.270
A second chance!

11:28.896 --> 11:29.855
Second what now?

11:29.939 --> 11:33.984
-We are going to the Mambo Cabana!
-The Mambo the what what?

11:36.070 --> 11:37.655
♪ There is a place ♪

11:38.823 --> 11:43.577
♪ Many miles away
Where the rhythm digs in deep ♪

11:44.620 --> 11:47.665
♪ And won't let go, that's how you know ♪

11:47.748 --> 11:50.251
♪ You've reached the Mambo Cabana ♪

11:51.752 --> 11:52.920
[gasps]

11:53.003 --> 11:54.797
♪ Your heart will race ♪

11:55.631 --> 12:00.386
♪ Horns will start to play
And banish any hope of sleep ♪

12:01.137 --> 12:04.515
♪ This is my chance
To share another dance ♪

12:04.598 --> 12:07.226
♪ In the Mambo Cabana ♪

12:07.309 --> 12:09.812
♪ Mambo Cabana, Cabana, Cabana ♪

12:09.895 --> 12:13.983
♪ Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!
Slow down, things are moving too fast ♪

12:14.066 --> 12:18.237
♪ We leave the old hometown
With this note from the past ♪

12:18.320 --> 12:19.447
♪ No, no, no, no! ♪

12:19.530 --> 12:24.577
♪ Stay home in this life that we've made
With the songs that we've played ♪

12:24.660 --> 12:27.872
♪ Vivo, don't be afraid! ♪

12:27.955 --> 12:31.167
♪ It's not too late ♪

12:32.168 --> 12:36.213
♪ It's not too late ♪

12:36.297 --> 12:42.052
-♪ It's not too late ♪
-[Vivo screams]

12:42.136 --> 12:43.471
-[Vivo grunts]
-[Andrés chuckles]

12:43.554 --> 12:45.931
[Vivo] What is happening?

12:53.355 --> 12:56.734
♪ I can see and hear it all, mi amigo ♪

12:57.485 --> 13:01.405
-♪ Entertaining in that hall, contigo ♪
-What? Wait!

13:01.489 --> 13:04.742
♪ And Marta singing so fine ♪

13:04.825 --> 13:09.663
♪ But the melody she sings is mine
Like… ♪

13:09.747 --> 13:14.251
♪ La, la, la, la, la, la, la
La, la, la ♪

13:14.335 --> 13:16.462
♪ It's not too late ♪

13:16.545 --> 13:18.005
Andrés!

13:18.088 --> 13:20.925
♪ La, la, la, la la
La, la, la, la ♪

13:21.008 --> 13:22.676
♪ Mambo Cabana ♪

13:22.760 --> 13:26.430
[Marta] ♪ It's not too late, ah! ♪

13:26.514 --> 13:28.933
-[Vivo yelps]
-♪ Pa' la cabana, Mambo Cabana ♪

13:29.016 --> 13:33.062
-[Andrés and Marta] ♪ It's not too late ♪
-♪ Pa' la cabana, Mambo Cabana ♪

13:33.145 --> 13:35.439
♪ It's not too late ♪

13:36.106 --> 13:37.483
¡Vamos mañana!

13:39.819 --> 13:41.612
♪ The Mambo Cabana ♪

13:43.280 --> 13:45.407
-[Andrés grunts]
-[Vivo chirps angrily]

13:45.491 --> 13:48.035
Ha! I can't believe
you're seriously considering this.

13:48.118 --> 13:49.703
[chittering frantically]

13:49.787 --> 13:52.039
Oh, Vivo, you are excited too, eh?

13:52.122 --> 13:53.666
No! I'm not excited.

13:53.749 --> 13:55.960
We're not Miami guys.
We're small-town guys.

13:56.043 --> 14:00.005
-We're plaza guys.
-Don't worry. Everything will be okay.

14:00.089 --> 14:01.632
[chittering angrily]

14:01.715 --> 14:02.675
Catch!

14:03.217 --> 14:04.718
[growls]

14:04.802 --> 14:06.971
-[giggling]
-Hey!

14:07.054 --> 14:07.888
[harrumphs]

14:09.765 --> 14:10.599
[sighs]

14:13.269 --> 14:14.770
Listen, Vivo.

14:14.854 --> 14:17.648
I must deliver this song to Marta.

14:18.190 --> 14:20.317
She needs to know that I love her.

14:21.277 --> 14:23.028
It's only one song.

14:23.112 --> 14:24.280
[chittering angrily]

14:24.363 --> 14:25.865
[in Spanish] I need you, my son!

14:28.742 --> 14:30.369
Hey, Vivo, where are you going?

14:31.912 --> 14:32.913
Mmm…

14:34.665 --> 14:36.166
[sighing] Ay, Vivo.

14:41.547 --> 14:44.383
What is he thinking?
A plane trip to Miami.

14:44.466 --> 14:48.470
It's been 60 years, and you go
all the way there for one show?

14:48.554 --> 14:50.014
For one song?

14:51.056 --> 14:53.267
What difference can one song make?

14:55.603 --> 14:58.647
[guitar playing in distance]

14:59.273 --> 15:01.108
[birds chirping]

15:27.426 --> 15:28.385
[chitters]

15:32.765 --> 15:33.599
[chuckles]

15:35.935 --> 15:37.645
-[maraca rattling]
-[Vivo exclaims]

15:46.362 --> 15:47.196
What am I doing?

15:49.073 --> 15:49.949
Come on, Vivo.

15:50.783 --> 15:53.035
[uplifting guitar music playing]

15:54.787 --> 15:55.913
[sighs]

15:55.996 --> 15:57.206
[Andrés snoring]

16:13.305 --> 16:15.808
[chuckles]
That suitcase isn't gonna pack itself.

16:30.114 --> 16:31.323
[groans]

16:33.575 --> 16:34.827
[exhales] Okay.

16:39.289 --> 16:41.750
[sighs] Beautiful day to travel.

16:43.335 --> 16:44.378
Good morning.

16:45.587 --> 16:49.049
Look, I'm really sorry about last night.

16:49.591 --> 16:50.884
But I think we--

16:54.221 --> 16:55.139
Andrés?

17:11.488 --> 17:12.322
[gasps]

17:12.406 --> 17:14.158
[wind whooshes]

17:31.884 --> 17:33.385
[panting]

17:33.927 --> 17:35.304
[grunting]

17:39.641 --> 17:41.185
[panting] Oof!

17:52.946 --> 17:53.781
[sighs]

17:55.157 --> 17:57.159
[panting]

17:58.994 --> 17:59.828
[sniffles]

18:01.914 --> 18:02.956
[cries softly]

18:07.336 --> 18:10.923
[melancholy music playing]

18:28.607 --> 18:31.944
Havana lost a good friend
in Andrés Hernández.

18:33.237 --> 18:36.698
For years, the sound of his tres
filled this plaza

18:37.324 --> 18:38.992
and our hearts.

18:39.076 --> 18:40.285
We were all so excited

18:40.369 --> 18:44.331
for news that he would soon be reunited
with Marta Sandoval.

18:45.541 --> 18:48.710
But alas, it was not meant to be.

18:48.794 --> 18:49.628
[whimpers]

18:50.838 --> 18:52.172
Ay, señora.

18:58.387 --> 18:59.596
Ay, muchas gracias.

19:00.139 --> 19:02.141
My name is Rosa Hernández.

19:02.808 --> 19:03.642
[sighs]

19:04.101 --> 19:06.812
Andrés was my late husband's uncle.

19:07.354 --> 19:09.773
My daughter Gabriela and I
are from Florida.

19:09.857 --> 19:11.441
This is our first trip to Cuba.

19:11.525 --> 19:14.361
-[Rosa speaking in background]
-Psst. Hey. That's my mom.

19:14.444 --> 19:15.320
[chirps inquisitively]

19:16.780 --> 19:18.198
My name is Gabi.

19:18.282 --> 19:20.200
-You're Vivo, right?
-[chitters softly]

19:20.868 --> 19:23.245
Hey, I know what you're going through.

19:23.871 --> 19:26.415
-I lost my dad too.
-[whimpers]

19:26.498 --> 19:28.584
Carlos's connection to Cuba

19:28.667 --> 19:33.297
was a bond that neither time
nor distance could ever break.

19:33.380 --> 19:35.841
Unbreakable bonds.

19:35.924 --> 19:39.261
That's what we got.
Family takes care of family, right?

19:39.344 --> 19:40.179
[chirps]

19:40.262 --> 19:43.932
See, you get it. Wait! I got a great idea.

19:44.016 --> 19:46.602
You should come live with me in Florida.

19:47.144 --> 19:50.522
Yeah, we're going home tomorrow.
Come on, get in the bag.

19:53.275 --> 19:55.194
Wait, wait, Vivo. Where are you going?

19:55.277 --> 19:57.738
Are you worried about
where you'll be going to the bathroom?

19:57.821 --> 20:00.365
It's okay. I got wipes in here.

20:00.449 --> 20:01.909
So I thank you so much

20:01.992 --> 20:04.494
for receiving Gabriela and I
with open arms.

20:04.578 --> 20:06.288
Gracias, señora.

20:06.371 --> 20:08.498
[sighs] Ahora, amigos,

20:08.582 --> 20:12.336
let's all take this moment
to say our goodbyes as we listen to

20:12.419 --> 20:15.839
one more song for Andrés Hernández.

20:15.923 --> 20:16.757
[whimpers]

20:17.966 --> 20:19.718
[somber music plays]

20:55.295 --> 20:58.715
♪ You spent your life making music ♪

21:00.926 --> 21:03.553
♪ I thought the songs would never end ♪

21:06.098 --> 21:08.433
♪ Now it's so quiet ♪

21:11.645 --> 21:14.898
♪ All I wanna do
Is play again with you, my friend ♪

21:17.484 --> 21:21.280
♪ You fell asleep humming music ♪

21:23.031 --> 21:25.867
♪ The sun came up, you stayed at rest ♪

21:28.036 --> 21:30.580
♪ Now here I am ♪

21:33.583 --> 21:36.086
♪ All I have left is one request ♪

21:36.628 --> 21:39.548
♪ One more song, just one more ♪

21:39.631 --> 21:42.259
♪ Give us an encore, don't go away ♪

21:42.342 --> 21:44.886
♪ We still have music to play ♪

21:45.929 --> 21:50.392
♪ Hey! I said one more song
Just one more ♪

21:50.475 --> 21:54.229
♪ All that I long for, give me a sign
It's not too late ♪

21:55.439 --> 21:58.400
♪ It's not too late ♪

21:59.568 --> 22:02.404
[crowd] ♪ One more song, one more song ♪

22:04.906 --> 22:07.659
♪ One more song, one more song ♪

22:10.370 --> 22:12.873
♪ One more song, one more song ♪

22:12.956 --> 22:16.335
♪ If you live on
It's through your music ♪

22:16.418 --> 22:18.253
♪ One more song, one more song ♪

22:18.337 --> 22:20.797
♪ A song for someone else to hear ♪

22:20.881 --> 22:22.799
♪ One more song, one more song ♪

22:22.883 --> 22:26.470
♪ So I'll take it home where it belongs ♪

22:26.553 --> 22:28.263
♪ One more song, one more song ♪

22:28.347 --> 22:31.433
♪ All I have to do
Is sing louder than my fear ♪

22:31.516 --> 22:35.604
♪ I need you here for one more song ♪

22:35.687 --> 22:39.816
♪ Just one more
You need an encore, I need to go ♪

22:39.900 --> 22:42.569
♪ Get there in time for the show ♪

22:43.236 --> 22:46.281
♪ Let everybody know
There's one more song ♪

22:46.365 --> 22:50.327
♪ Just one more
Time to be strong for the journey ahead ♪

22:50.410 --> 22:53.038
♪ Sing through the doubt
Sing through the dread ♪

22:53.121 --> 22:55.665
♪ With a scream and a shout
Break through the fear ♪

22:55.749 --> 22:57.376
♪ Like the sun through the clouds ♪

22:57.459 --> 22:59.628
♪ Like you're still here
No crying allowed ♪

22:59.711 --> 23:02.297
♪ I'll try to get out
I'll try to be strong ♪

23:02.381 --> 23:04.049
♪ Yes, I'm moving on ♪

23:04.549 --> 23:11.431
♪ It's time for one more song ♪

23:15.894 --> 23:18.105
-[recorder playing unmelodiously]
-[Vivo] Ah!

23:22.818 --> 23:24.236
[groans] It's the weird kid.

23:24.736 --> 23:26.696
Gabi, what are you doing?

23:26.780 --> 23:27.989
Just playing a tune.

23:28.073 --> 23:30.867
Maybe Vivo will hear it,
and I can take him back to Florida.

23:30.951 --> 23:32.828
Oh, that's right. She's from Florida.

23:32.911 --> 23:35.497
Gabriela, what did I say? No more pets.

23:35.580 --> 23:38.208
-Please?
-No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

23:38.291 --> 23:41.294
And besides, we cannot take
a wild animal on a plane.

23:41.378 --> 23:42.212
Ugh.

23:42.295 --> 23:44.172
[Montoya] Señora Hernández! [panting]

23:45.006 --> 23:47.426
So glad I caught you before you left.

23:47.509 --> 23:48.343
[grunts]

23:49.344 --> 23:50.345
Gabi, mi niña,

23:51.012 --> 23:54.516
we know you love music,
just like your Uncle Andrés.

23:54.599 --> 23:59.229
So, we wanted to see you off
with a few of his musical mementos.

23:59.312 --> 24:01.731
Vintage maracas! Claves!

24:01.815 --> 24:05.986
Ho ho! Check out this bad boy! [laughs]

24:06.069 --> 24:10.615
Oh, thank you, Montoya.
You gave my kid an accordion.

24:10.699 --> 24:12.033
You feeling it, Mom?

24:12.117 --> 24:14.578
[in Spanish] Ah, what a beautiful thing.

24:14.661 --> 24:16.538
-[Rosa scoffs]
-Music is in her blood.

24:17.497 --> 24:20.500
-[Gabi] Cuba! Cuba! I love Cuban music.
-[Vivo] Oh!

24:22.002 --> 24:24.421
[gasps] That's it. Marta, here I come.

24:24.504 --> 24:27.132
[Gabi] What's up, Cuba?
I'll give you a backbeat.

24:27.215 --> 24:28.633
[beatboxes poorly]

24:28.717 --> 24:30.760
[Rosa] Thank you. Thank you, Gabi.

24:30.844 --> 24:33.388
I'm sure all of Cuba knows you're here.

24:33.472 --> 24:36.892
Sorry. Guess my playing
was a little too hardcore.

24:36.975 --> 24:39.019
Playing? That noise was playing? [yelps]

24:41.354 --> 24:43.690
Ah, bueno. Here's your taxi.

24:43.773 --> 24:45.233
Montoya, thank you.

24:45.317 --> 24:47.068
¡Gracias, Montoya!

24:47.152 --> 24:49.863
Adiós. Practice that music every day.

24:49.946 --> 24:52.908
[electronic music playing]

25:13.512 --> 25:15.514
Ugh, my head.

25:16.389 --> 25:18.183
I guess traveling is not my thing.

25:18.934 --> 25:20.143
[grunts]

25:21.061 --> 25:24.689
Where am I? What time is it?
What time is it? What time is it?

25:25.899 --> 25:28.360
Okay, 10 a.m. Still have ten hours.

25:31.029 --> 25:33.573
Oh, right. It's the backpack kid.

25:33.657 --> 25:36.660
Look what I got. Hmm? Hmm?

25:36.743 --> 25:40.747
-Are you excited about today?
-Oh, yeah, of course. What's today?

25:40.830 --> 25:44.000
It's your first cookie sale
with the Sand Dollar Troop.

25:44.084 --> 25:44.960
Woot woot!

25:45.043 --> 25:47.212
Yeah, I don't think that's gonna happen.

25:47.295 --> 25:50.507
I've taken the Sand Dollars
about as far as I can.

25:50.590 --> 25:53.885
[Rosa] Gabi, what are you talking about?
You've only been to one meeting.

25:53.969 --> 25:55.303
[Gabi] I know.

25:55.387 --> 25:57.889
-But it's time to move on.
-[Rosa] Move on?

25:58.473 --> 26:01.601
[sighs] You just started with the troop.
You're still getting to know them.

26:01.685 --> 26:03.937
Ha! Tail never fails.

26:04.938 --> 26:05.981
[yelps]

26:06.064 --> 26:08.108
Please, give them a chance.

26:08.191 --> 26:10.235
Look, I made my resignation video.

26:10.318 --> 26:12.654
-Cookies!
-[hip-hop music plays]

26:12.737 --> 26:15.240
Peace. We out. Bye.

26:15.323 --> 26:17.325
[cell phone beeps, booms]

26:18.034 --> 26:19.786
-Creative.
-[Gabi] Wait, wait, wait!

26:19.869 --> 26:23.873
This is the best part.
I turned them into zombie clowns.

26:23.957 --> 26:26.626
[grotesquely] Buy my cookies.

26:26.710 --> 26:29.838
Gabriela Maria Rosa Hernández,
you are a part of that troop.

26:29.921 --> 26:32.632
They're counting on you.
You can't just abandon them.

26:32.716 --> 26:33.883
-[Gabi] Why?
-[squeals]

26:34.884 --> 26:37.971
Pulgita, you can't keep pushing
everyone away.

26:38.597 --> 26:42.350
If you don't at least try
to get along with other kids,

26:42.434 --> 26:44.436
you're going to be very lonely.

26:45.854 --> 26:46.688
Meh.

26:47.272 --> 26:49.691
Gabriela, escúchame. You're doing this!

26:49.774 --> 26:52.277
I let you keep
that… that… that… that purple hair.

26:52.360 --> 26:53.194
You owe me one!

26:53.278 --> 26:56.948
But, Mom, all they ever talk about
are selling cookies,

26:57.032 --> 26:59.701
getting badges, saving the Everglades.

26:59.784 --> 27:01.995
It's so boring!

27:02.078 --> 27:05.832
You're going to the cookie sale.
You're going to take selfies.

27:05.915 --> 27:08.627
And you're going to have fun and bond!

27:08.710 --> 27:11.546
Now put on the uniform. It's really cute.

27:13.882 --> 27:14.716
[sighs]

27:14.799 --> 27:16.176
-[microwaves beeps]
-[gasps]

27:20.305 --> 27:21.973
Blah, blah, blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.

27:24.976 --> 27:26.895
Coast is clear. Let's get out of here.

27:27.395 --> 27:28.271
[whimpers softly]

27:29.397 --> 27:31.066
[grunting]

27:33.443 --> 27:34.277
[Vivo yelps]

27:38.615 --> 27:42.827
-[accordion squeaking]
-[Vivo] Ow! Ow! Whoa! Ow!

27:43.620 --> 27:45.121
[grunting]

27:45.205 --> 27:46.748
Ow! Ow!

27:47.707 --> 27:49.459
[yelping]

27:49.542 --> 27:53.963
It's fine. It's just the belongings
of your dearly departed great uncle.

27:54.047 --> 27:56.424
Rolling on the floor, all by itself.

27:56.508 --> 27:59.761
Playing spooky accordion music.

28:02.472 --> 28:03.431
[squeaks]

28:08.603 --> 28:11.564
It's fine. [laughs nervously, groans]

28:16.361 --> 28:17.946
[panting]

28:20.323 --> 28:21.157
[gasping]

28:29.791 --> 28:33.712
-[shrieking]
-[screaming]

28:33.795 --> 28:35.588
-[Vivo chitters]
-[giggles]

28:35.672 --> 28:38.341
-Vivo, you're here!
-Yup. And now I'm leaving.

28:39.759 --> 28:42.470
-You followed me, didn't you?
-[coos]

28:42.554 --> 28:44.264
And you snuck in my bag

28:45.014 --> 28:46.391
because you love me!

28:46.474 --> 28:49.436
-[squeaks in protest]
-I'm so glad you're here, Vivo.

28:49.519 --> 28:52.522
[gasps] Now I have someone
to share my friendship bracelet with.

28:52.605 --> 28:54.399
Best friends forever!

28:54.482 --> 28:57.110
-Hey, let go. Paws to yourself.
-Hold still.

28:57.193 --> 28:58.027
[Vivo squeals]

28:58.111 --> 29:01.239
Forever's a long time, kid!
I have a song to deliver. [yelps]

29:01.322 --> 29:04.200
-[Gabi giggles]
-[yelps] Nice meeting you. Peace!

29:05.160 --> 29:08.747
[dramatic music plays]

29:10.665 --> 29:12.667
Are those little gravestones?

29:12.751 --> 29:14.085
Oh, that's my petting zoo.

29:14.919 --> 29:16.421
Well, it was.

29:17.338 --> 29:18.173
[Rosa] Gabi?

29:18.256 --> 29:19.466
It's my Mom. Hide.

29:19.549 --> 29:21.217
-[Vivo shrieks]
-[toys clatter]

29:22.969 --> 29:24.471
'Sup, Mom? [laughs nervously]

29:24.554 --> 29:27.265
Why did I just find this in the microwave?

29:27.348 --> 29:30.101
I was drying it?

29:30.185 --> 29:32.645
You were dr-- [gasps] What is that?

29:34.063 --> 29:37.859
How many times have I told you?
No food in the room.

29:37.942 --> 29:39.819
We're going to attract animals.

29:39.903 --> 29:42.030
Here, take your uniform.

29:42.113 --> 29:44.574
[groans] You mean my invisibility cloak?

29:44.657 --> 29:47.619
-Gabi.
-I can feel hives coming on.

29:47.702 --> 29:49.871
My throat is getting itchy.

29:49.954 --> 29:51.998
It's a uniform, not an allergy.

29:52.081 --> 29:53.541
Here. Hurry up and change.

29:53.625 --> 29:55.293
We don't wanna be late
for the cookie sale.

29:55.376 --> 29:57.003
[muttering] Yes, I do.

29:58.046 --> 29:59.172
-[sighs]
-[Vivo grunts]

29:59.255 --> 30:00.298
Did you see that, Vivo?

30:01.174 --> 30:03.718
-She doesn't get me at all.
-[drums bang]

30:03.802 --> 30:05.845
She wants me to wear a uniform

30:05.929 --> 30:07.514
just like everyone else.

30:07.597 --> 30:10.683
-[guitar strums]
-But I'm not like everyone else, because…

30:11.351 --> 30:13.770
♪ I bounce to the beat of my own drum ♪

30:13.853 --> 30:16.105
♪ I'm a wow in a world full of ho-hum ♪

30:16.189 --> 30:18.358
♪ I'm a wild young lady
But you know 'sum? ♪

30:18.441 --> 30:20.610
♪ I'd rather be at home with my own drum ♪

30:20.693 --> 30:22.862
♪ I bounce to the beat of my own drum ♪

30:22.946 --> 30:25.156
♪ I'm a wow in a world full of ho-hum ♪

30:25.240 --> 30:27.408
♪ I'm a wild young lady
But you know 'sum? ♪

30:27.492 --> 30:29.786
♪ I'd rather be at home with my own drum ♪

30:29.869 --> 30:32.080
♪ I had a violin
But I wrecked the rental ♪

30:32.163 --> 30:34.499
♪ I play the tambourine
And I'm never gentle ♪

30:34.582 --> 30:36.584
♪ See what I mean?
That was accidental ♪

30:36.668 --> 30:38.878
♪ But now that we're a team
We'll be instrumental ♪

30:38.962 --> 30:41.381
[gasps] ♪ Instrumental, ha!
See what I did there? ♪

30:41.464 --> 30:43.633
♪ I made a pun, ha!
I'm having fun, ha! ♪

30:43.716 --> 30:44.926
♪ I'm never done, ha! ♪

30:45.009 --> 30:47.804
♪ I'm just a one young woman
Ba rum pa pum pum ♪

30:47.887 --> 30:50.056
♪ I bounce to the beat of my own drum ♪

30:50.139 --> 30:52.308
♪ I'm a wow in a world full of ho-hum ♪

30:52.392 --> 30:54.602
♪ I'm a wild young lady
But you know 'sum? ♪

30:54.686 --> 30:57.063
♪ I'd rather be at home with my own drum ♪

30:57.146 --> 31:00.441
♪ Extra, extra! Read all about it
I'm extra, extra ♪

31:00.525 --> 31:02.694
♪ The kid that the other kids
Can't get next to ♪

31:02.777 --> 31:06.239
♪ I got my own seat on the bus
I've always been a me, not an us ♪

31:06.322 --> 31:08.533
-♪ "You're at a ten" ♪
-♪ "I need you at a three," ha! ♪

31:08.616 --> 31:10.660
♪ Try that again
I gotta be me, yo ♪

31:10.743 --> 31:12.787
♪ I am a ten
I gotta be free ♪

31:12.871 --> 31:15.164
♪ And I got a friend
We're a team and we… ♪

31:15.248 --> 31:17.208
♪ Bounce to the beat of our own drum ♪

31:17.292 --> 31:19.460
♪ We're a wow in a world full of ho-hum ♪

31:19.544 --> 31:21.754
♪ I'm a wild young lady
But you know 'sum? ♪

31:21.838 --> 31:24.340
♪ I'd rather be at home with my own drum
Solo! ♪

31:24.424 --> 31:26.217
[recorder playing enthusiastically]

31:33.516 --> 31:35.518
[in Auto-Tune] ♪ Ha! Now that's a solo ♪

31:36.019 --> 31:37.437
♪ I've always flown solo ♪

31:37.520 --> 31:39.772
♪ I speed up when the world's in slo-mo ♪

31:39.856 --> 31:42.025
♪ Make it up as I go when I don't know ♪

31:42.108 --> 31:44.652
♪ And I know
I know it seems like I'm lonely ♪

31:44.736 --> 31:46.529
♪ People assume that I'm lonely ♪

31:46.613 --> 31:49.365
♪ Look at this room
And assume that you know me, homey ♪

31:49.449 --> 31:51.451
♪ You don't know me
I'm in the zone! ♪

31:51.534 --> 31:53.369
[vocals echoing]

31:53.453 --> 31:55.872
♪ We bounce to the beat of our own drum ♪

31:55.955 --> 31:58.207
♪ We're a wow in a world full of ho-hum ♪

31:58.291 --> 32:00.293
♪ I'm a wild young lady
But you know 'sum? ♪

32:00.376 --> 32:02.420
♪ I'd rather be at home with my own drum ♪

32:02.503 --> 32:04.756
♪ We bounce to the beat of our own drum ♪

32:04.839 --> 32:07.008
♪ We're a wow in a world full of ho-hum ♪

32:07.091 --> 32:09.427
♪ I'm a wild young lady
But you know 'sum? ♪

32:09.510 --> 32:11.846
♪ I'd rather be at home with my own drum ♪

32:11.930 --> 32:12.972
♪ Bounce! ♪

32:13.056 --> 32:14.015
[giggles]

32:14.098 --> 32:16.351
-♪ Bounce! ♪
-♪ Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey! ♪

32:16.434 --> 32:18.519
-♪ Bounce! ♪
-♪ Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey! ♪

32:18.603 --> 32:20.229
-♪ Bounce! ♪
-♪ Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey! ♪

32:21.189 --> 32:22.482
♪ Where'd you go, huh? ♪

32:24.275 --> 32:25.360
What's this?

32:28.655 --> 32:29.489
[gasps]

32:29.572 --> 32:31.282
[grunting]

32:32.158 --> 32:34.661
Phew!
That girl is a whole lot of something.

32:35.161 --> 32:37.163
-[kids laughing]
-[neighbors conversing]

32:37.246 --> 32:39.165
[Vivo] So, this is Florida?

32:39.248 --> 32:41.751
[steel drum music playing]

32:43.127 --> 32:44.337
Huh.

32:45.463 --> 32:47.507
Oh. Plastic birds.

32:48.675 --> 32:49.717
Florida's weird.

32:52.345 --> 32:54.097
Now all I have to do is find Marta.

32:54.973 --> 32:57.141
Come on, Andrés.
I need some kind of a sign.

32:57.809 --> 33:01.145
Anything. Point the way. Any sign will do.

33:03.398 --> 33:05.608
[uplifting music playing]

33:08.319 --> 33:10.279
Mambo Cabana.

33:10.363 --> 33:11.239
[man] Excuse me.

33:11.322 --> 33:14.409
-Is this the bus to Miami?
-Yes, sir, it is.

33:14.492 --> 33:17.203
[Vivo] Perfect. Mambo Cabana, here I come.

33:17.286 --> 33:21.207
♪ Do, do, it's not too late
I'm gonna take the bus right there ♪

33:21.290 --> 33:23.668
♪ Hello, hello ♪ [vocalizing]

33:23.751 --> 33:24.752
Is this seat taken?

33:24.836 --> 33:27.005
-[passengers scream]
-[woman] It's a ferret!

33:27.547 --> 33:30.091
Hey! No pets,
no critters, whatever you are.

33:30.174 --> 33:31.843
-Get off of my bus.
-[Vivo grunts]

33:31.926 --> 33:33.428
Not on my watch.

33:33.511 --> 33:34.887
[passengers cheer]

33:34.971 --> 33:38.224
Oh, you like that?
I came up with that myself.

33:38.307 --> 33:40.852
[indistinct chatter]

33:40.935 --> 33:43.563
Aw, you are adorable.

33:43.646 --> 33:45.606
Uh, thank you?

33:45.690 --> 33:47.150
Probably tasty too.

33:47.900 --> 33:49.152
[Vivo screams]

33:49.235 --> 33:51.154
[barking]

33:51.237 --> 33:52.363
No! Get away!

33:53.072 --> 33:53.906
[yelping]

34:05.251 --> 34:06.169
[blows raspberry]

34:07.670 --> 34:09.839
-[Gabi] There you are!
-[gasps] No, no, no, no, no!

34:09.922 --> 34:13.468
I know why you came to Florida.
You're trying to find Marta.

34:14.594 --> 34:16.012
I read Marta's letter.

34:16.679 --> 34:20.600
Tío Andrés wanted to be
at her show tonight, didn't he?

34:22.351 --> 34:23.436
[chirps]

34:23.519 --> 34:25.730
Are you trying to get there too?

34:25.813 --> 34:26.939
[chitters]

34:27.023 --> 34:28.649
But… but why?

34:29.484 --> 34:30.318
[sighs softly]

34:36.866 --> 34:37.784
What's this?

34:38.576 --> 34:40.369
"Para Marta"?

34:40.453 --> 34:42.663
Tío wrote her a song?

34:42.747 --> 34:43.748
[chitters]

34:43.831 --> 34:47.710
"Your plane leaves in the morning.
Soon the world will see you shine."

34:47.794 --> 34:52.924
"And I wish I could go with you,
but your journey isn't mine."

34:54.092 --> 34:56.594
[gasps] You know what this means?

34:57.428 --> 34:58.846
He never got to say,

34:59.514 --> 35:00.681
"I love you."

35:05.228 --> 35:08.856
Vivo, this is really important.
Marta needs to hear this song.

35:08.940 --> 35:10.817
And I'm gonna get you there.

35:10.900 --> 35:12.944
[sighs in relief] You are?

35:14.695 --> 35:15.988
Marta's final show

35:16.072 --> 35:18.991
is at the Mambo Cabana in Miami.

35:19.075 --> 35:21.994
We don't have much time.
But don't worry. I have a plan.

35:22.870 --> 35:24.664
First, get in my bag.

35:25.790 --> 35:27.416
[gasps] Ugh!

35:28.251 --> 35:31.337
Anything for Andrés.
Anything for Andrés. Anything for Andrés.

35:31.420 --> 35:32.255
[retches]

35:32.338 --> 35:36.384
But it's Marta Sandoval's last show ever!

35:36.467 --> 35:37.635
-Come on, Mom,
-[Rosa] What?

35:37.718 --> 35:39.262
Miami isn't that far.

35:39.345 --> 35:41.973
Since when
are you such a Marta Sandoval fan?

35:42.056 --> 35:45.226
Since I was born. I'm a huge fan.

35:45.309 --> 35:47.353
Name one song.

35:47.436 --> 35:51.023
Uh, "Despacito"?

35:52.191 --> 35:55.319
Get ready for the cookie sale.
I'm not going to tell you again.

35:56.028 --> 35:56.863
[groans]

35:57.363 --> 36:00.867
-Don't worry, I have another better idea.
-[Vivo gasps for air]

36:00.950 --> 36:04.453
Does it involve cleaning your backpack?
'Cause there's a lot of stuff in there.

36:04.537 --> 36:06.956
Wipes are none of them. I saw no wipes.

36:07.039 --> 36:08.374
Let's see.

36:08.457 --> 36:10.793
Key West to Miami.

36:12.003 --> 36:15.214
Perfect. This will get us there
in time for the show.

36:15.965 --> 36:19.427
-[mambo music playing]
-Mambo Cabana, here we come.

36:21.512 --> 36:23.264
[in Spanish] ♪ Say present ♪

36:23.347 --> 36:27.059
♪ Say present, that's it! ♪

36:27.143 --> 36:29.353
[man] Marta, mi amor, I love you.

36:29.437 --> 36:30.521
[woman] Marta!

36:31.814 --> 36:35.276
Señora Sandoval,
it is such an honor to meet you.

36:35.359 --> 36:37.987
-Muchas gracias.
-Right this way.

36:38.070 --> 36:41.157
I can't tell you how proud we are
that you chose the Mambo Cabana

36:41.240 --> 36:42.325
for your final show.

36:43.201 --> 36:44.118
Marta.

36:44.202 --> 36:47.914
Is it true that your old partner Andrés
might play with you tonight?

36:48.539 --> 36:49.540
One can hope.

36:51.834 --> 36:55.880
[Gabi] Welcome
to beautiful downtown Key West.

36:55.963 --> 36:58.007
Step one, bus tickets.

37:00.718 --> 37:02.220
Now, remember, stay in my bag,

37:02.303 --> 37:04.931
and if anyone asks,
you're my emotional support animal.

37:05.014 --> 37:06.349
[Troop girls] Cookies!

37:06.432 --> 37:08.017
Cookie sale.

37:08.100 --> 37:11.604
All proceeds
go to protecting endangered species.

37:11.687 --> 37:13.564
Oh no, the Sand Dollars.

37:13.648 --> 37:17.318
Oh, Mr. Henshaw. Can I interest you
in some Manatee Minties?

37:17.401 --> 37:20.863
Did you know the Everglades are home
to 2,000 species of plants and animals?

37:20.947 --> 37:22.865
And 70 of those are endanger-- [gasps]

37:23.366 --> 37:27.078
Oh, excuse me. [chuckles] You know
that if you buy a Sand Dollars cloth bag

37:27.161 --> 37:29.080
instead of using a plastic one,

37:29.163 --> 37:31.791
then you won't have the blood
of Mother Nature on your hands.

37:31.874 --> 37:33.709
I'm not a bad man.

37:34.418 --> 37:35.836
I just want a cookie.

37:35.920 --> 37:39.048
[baby crying]

37:40.216 --> 37:41.384
[grumbles]

37:41.467 --> 37:43.469
We gotta get out of here
before they see us.

37:43.552 --> 37:44.762
[Troop girl] Hernández!

37:44.845 --> 37:47.932
Oh, hello, blonde one.

37:48.432 --> 37:49.642
Other girls.

37:49.725 --> 37:51.102
Gabi, where's your uniform?

37:51.227 --> 37:54.146
Yes, we have rules, Hernández.
[clears throat]

37:54.230 --> 37:58.484
Only a Sand Dollar in full uniform
may participate in a cookie sale.

37:58.567 --> 37:59.777
What?

37:59.860 --> 38:03.656
The cookie sale is today?
I totally thought that was yesterday.

38:03.739 --> 38:05.866
But you didn't show up
yesterday either, did ya?

38:05.950 --> 38:07.326
That's a good point.

38:07.410 --> 38:10.621
I was busy rescuing this animal.

38:10.705 --> 38:11.622
[grunts nervously]

38:11.706 --> 38:12.790
[both] Aw!

38:12.873 --> 38:15.501
-What are you doing?
-Oh, he's so cute.

38:15.584 --> 38:16.627
Can I pet him?

38:16.711 --> 38:18.879
-No.
-Go to town. He loves it.

38:18.963 --> 38:20.172
-Look at that face.
-Aw!

38:20.256 --> 38:23.259
-He's adorable.
-Hey! Stop. This is borderline abuse.

38:23.342 --> 38:25.469
-His little ears! Oh!
-So fuzzy. What's his name?

38:25.553 --> 38:29.056
His name's Vivo. And he's a possum.

38:29.140 --> 38:31.726
-[Vivo grunts]
-Gabi, that's not a possum.

38:31.809 --> 38:33.185
[scoffs] That's a kinkajou.

38:33.269 --> 38:35.896
A very rare South American
tropical rain forest mammal,

38:35.980 --> 38:37.231
aka the honey bear.

38:37.315 --> 38:39.275
The honey bear?
Never heard it, but I'll take it.

38:39.900 --> 38:41.694
His eyes look a little cloudy.

38:41.777 --> 38:43.946
His coat is kinda mangy.

38:44.530 --> 38:45.990
Has he seen a veterinarian?

38:46.073 --> 38:47.408
Uh, sorry, what?

38:47.491 --> 38:50.119
[scoffs] Gabi, there are rules
to be followed.

38:50.202 --> 38:54.123
For his own safety, he needs vaccinations
and a week of medical observation.

38:54.206 --> 38:55.750
-A week?
-[chittering]

38:55.833 --> 39:00.755
Yes. Isolated from other animals.
Didn't you read your Sand Dollars manual?

39:00.838 --> 39:04.467
Oh, yeah, the week. We did that.

39:04.550 --> 39:08.971
Oh, good. Then you wouldn't mind
showing me his vaccination certificate?

39:09.055 --> 39:11.640
Yeah, I'll get it right now.

39:11.724 --> 39:13.976
It's in the trunk of my bike.

39:15.186 --> 39:16.729
[gasps] No, no, no, no.

39:16.812 --> 39:18.689
-[chirps] Uh-oh.
-Time for plan B.

39:18.773 --> 39:21.984
Wait a minute.
Bikes don't have a trunk, right?

39:22.068 --> 39:25.154
You know, I'm starting to think
she doesn't have a certificate.

39:25.237 --> 39:27.156
Yeah, you think?

39:27.239 --> 39:30.618
Girls, we've got us
a Sand Dollar gone rogue.

39:31.243 --> 39:32.495
Move out!

39:32.578 --> 39:34.789
-[up-tempo music playing]
-[chirps anxiously]

39:34.914 --> 39:37.583
Change of plans.
We'll catch the bus at the next stop.

39:40.169 --> 39:41.921
-Pull over, Hernández!
-Oh no.

39:42.004 --> 39:43.255
Surrender the kinkajou!

39:43.339 --> 39:45.174
Don't worry, Vivo. I'll lose them.

39:45.257 --> 39:47.468
But what about the bus?
The plan was the bus.

39:48.260 --> 39:49.095
[tires screech]

39:51.430 --> 39:53.182
Well, that didn't work.

39:53.265 --> 39:55.810
Come on, Vivo.
Get back there and shake 'em off.

39:57.478 --> 40:00.689
Ha! Take that. How fun is this?

40:00.773 --> 40:04.819
And this should not be
in a child's backpack, but here you go!

40:05.736 --> 40:07.780
Hey! Oh, no, you didn't.

40:07.863 --> 40:09.615
Oh, there's the wipes. Ha!

40:09.698 --> 40:12.243
Stop! You stop right there,
you little-- Ah!

40:13.244 --> 40:14.078
Huh.

40:15.079 --> 40:16.747
Ha ha! Take that.

40:17.373 --> 40:18.332
[screams]

40:19.750 --> 40:21.961
He's dousing himself with chemicals!

40:22.044 --> 40:25.714
[gasps] It's a cry for help.
Gabi, give us the kinkajou!

40:26.632 --> 40:27.883
-[tires screech]
-Ah!

40:27.967 --> 40:29.009
Mr. Henshaw!

40:29.093 --> 40:30.469
You drove here?

40:30.553 --> 40:32.388
You live two blocks away!

40:32.471 --> 40:33.556
Shame on you!

40:33.639 --> 40:35.766
[both] Shame.

40:41.147 --> 40:44.024
You're in over your head, Hernández.
Give him up!

40:49.738 --> 40:52.616
[drawbridge signal dinging]

40:55.161 --> 40:56.787
Vivo, hold on tight.

40:56.871 --> 40:58.873
-We're gonna jump it!
-What?

41:00.541 --> 41:02.376
[Gabi] Yeah! Woo-hoo!

41:02.918 --> 41:05.880
All right, Miami, here we come.

41:07.006 --> 41:09.175
-Ah!
-No, no, no, no, no, no!

41:11.552 --> 41:13.304
-[Gabi] Huh.
-[drawbridge creaking]

41:15.014 --> 41:16.515
[Vivo screams]

41:18.893 --> 41:21.353
[foghorn blares]

41:23.689 --> 41:27.568
What have we done? We've allowed
that poor, defenseless creature

41:27.651 --> 41:31.238
to roam free in a world
where he surely won't survive.

41:31.739 --> 41:35.826
-So, back to the cookie booth?
-Cookie booth? Uh, no!

41:35.910 --> 41:38.954
It's our duty
as Sand Dollars to rescue him.

41:39.038 --> 41:39.872
Eva!

41:40.664 --> 41:41.832
Yeah?

41:41.916 --> 41:43.876
We're gonna need your dad's boat.

41:44.376 --> 41:46.754
[gasps, coughs]

41:46.837 --> 41:47.880
[panting]

41:48.631 --> 41:52.009
The song. Where is it? Where is it?
Where is… where is… where is…

41:52.551 --> 41:53.385
[gasps]

41:55.012 --> 41:56.430
[blows, sighs]

41:56.514 --> 41:58.474
Ah. Still in one piece.

41:59.183 --> 42:01.727
Okay, where are we? Where is that bus?

42:01.810 --> 42:03.729
-[foghorn blares]
-[gasps]

42:03.812 --> 42:06.857
[echoing] No!

42:07.483 --> 42:08.442
[gasps]

42:08.526 --> 42:10.736
[Gabi] Whee!

42:12.321 --> 42:13.697
Sand angels!

42:13.781 --> 42:15.741
Vivo, you should really try this.

42:15.824 --> 42:17.660
-[laughs gleefully]
-[exhales]

42:17.743 --> 42:20.412
Look at me. I'm a cat. Meow, meow.

42:20.496 --> 42:22.581
Ugh. I gotta get off this boat.

42:22.665 --> 42:23.749
-Hey, Vivo.
-[screams]

42:23.832 --> 42:27.378
I know we missed the bus,
but don't worry, I have a plan C.

42:27.461 --> 42:30.256
If we take a shortcut
through the Everglades National Park,

42:30.339 --> 42:31.799
we can make it before the show.

42:31.882 --> 42:32.716
[fanfare plays]

42:32.800 --> 42:35.719
Okay. New plan. Let's see.

42:38.138 --> 42:39.390
Hmm.

42:42.226 --> 42:43.060
Ha!

42:45.896 --> 42:46.730
[grunts]

42:48.941 --> 42:50.150
Ha!

42:50.234 --> 42:52.278
Whoa, Vivo, we're so in sync.

42:52.361 --> 42:54.822
-Just like a mind meld.
-[alarmed hooting]

42:56.782 --> 42:58.117
[pops, squeaks]

43:00.953 --> 43:02.788
-[bubble pops]
-[bicycle bell chimes]

43:02.871 --> 43:05.040
Oh man. I thought it could hold it.

43:05.499 --> 43:07.293
[angry muttering, screams]

43:07.376 --> 43:10.629
Mind meld? If we had a mind meld,
you'd be panicking,

43:10.713 --> 43:13.048
because that was our ticket to Miami.

43:13.132 --> 43:16.594
Now we're stuck on this giant boat
headed in the wrong direction.

43:16.677 --> 43:20.598
We couldn't be more out of sync.
This is what "in sync" sounds like.

43:20.681 --> 43:24.101
[mimicking rhythmic drums]

43:24.602 --> 43:26.645
This is you and me.

43:26.729 --> 43:30.482
[making discordant drum noises,
blowing raspberries]

43:30.566 --> 43:32.943
[angry screeching]

43:33.027 --> 43:35.487
We have totally different definitions
of the word "plan."

43:35.571 --> 43:39.033
To me and other rational people,
a plan revolves around the Five P's.

43:39.116 --> 43:40.993
Proper Planning
Prevents Poor Performance.

43:41.076 --> 43:42.244
But you,

43:42.328 --> 43:46.206
your plans are just bad impulses.

43:46.915 --> 43:48.000
What are you doing?

43:48.584 --> 43:52.755
-Ta-da! Sometimes you gotta improvise.
-[clip springs, clinks]

43:53.547 --> 43:54.757
Yeah, that will never float.

43:58.886 --> 44:02.139
-And the journey begins now!
-[screams]

44:03.557 --> 44:06.352
It floats. It actually floats.

44:06.435 --> 44:07.686
-Oh!
-[Gabi] Heads up.

44:07.770 --> 44:09.813
-[Vivo chitters angrily]
-[Gabi grunts]

44:09.897 --> 44:12.483
Give me a sec. [grunts]
Don't want to pull a hammy.

44:12.566 --> 44:14.902
[exhales] Okay. Ready, Vivo?

44:15.569 --> 44:17.571
Woo-hoo!

44:19.531 --> 44:20.908
And she missed.

44:20.991 --> 44:23.160
[laughing]

44:26.664 --> 44:28.791
I missed the boat completely.

44:28.874 --> 44:30.167
[chuckles]

44:30.250 --> 44:32.127
Did you see that, Vivo?

44:32.628 --> 44:34.588
Hysterical. [grunts]

44:34.672 --> 44:35.506
[chirps]

44:39.927 --> 44:42.638
Marta, here we come!

44:42.763 --> 44:44.139
[Vivo squeaks triumphantly]

44:56.985 --> 44:59.196
[Gabi's voice mail]
You have reached Gabi's robot.

44:59.279 --> 45:00.823
Leave a message. Beep.

45:00.906 --> 45:03.659
Gabi, I keep texting you.
Please call me back.

45:03.742 --> 45:05.119
We've talked about this.

45:05.202 --> 45:06.870
[in Spanish] ♪ Say present ♪

45:06.954 --> 45:11.250
-♪ Say present, that's it! ♪
-No, she wouldn't.

45:15.129 --> 45:16.380
She would.

45:21.260 --> 45:22.136
[sighs]

45:22.928 --> 45:25.639
Carlos, I could really use your help
right now.

45:29.685 --> 45:31.687
'Cause she gets this from you, you know.

45:32.354 --> 45:34.356
-[calm music playing]
-[birds cawing]

45:36.650 --> 45:38.652
♪ The plan was get to a bus ♪

45:38.736 --> 45:40.821
♪ Next thing you know, the two of us ♪

45:40.904 --> 45:43.866
♪ Are floating, drifting somewhere new ♪

45:45.117 --> 45:47.536
♪ She said we'd take a shortcut ♪

45:47.619 --> 45:50.247
-♪ I'm trying to be a good sport, but ♪
-[Gabi] Whoa!

45:50.330 --> 45:52.833
♪ I don't see how we make it through ♪

45:53.584 --> 45:57.713
♪ Remember the size of the world before ♪

45:57.796 --> 46:02.676
♪ It was you and I, just you and I ♪

46:02.760 --> 46:06.555
♪ And now the horizon holds so much more ♪

46:06.638 --> 46:08.766
♪ And it's do or die ♪

46:08.849 --> 46:11.268
♪ Yeah, it's do or die ♪

46:11.894 --> 46:16.273
♪ All I can do when the road bends ♪

46:16.356 --> 46:19.359
-[animals screeching in distance]
-♪ Is lean into the curve ♪

46:20.527 --> 46:25.532
♪ And all I can do
When the tank's run dry ♪

46:26.116 --> 46:28.035
♪ Is see what's in reserve ♪

46:29.411 --> 46:34.416
♪ And all I can do
When the plans break down ♪

46:34.917 --> 46:36.960
♪ Is stay on my feet ♪

46:38.295 --> 46:40.923
♪ And all I can do ♪

46:41.006 --> 46:44.468
♪ At the end of the day is play on ♪

46:44.551 --> 46:45.928
♪ Play on ♪

46:46.553 --> 46:47.638
♪ And keep the beat ♪

46:48.305 --> 46:50.682
-[frightened whimpering]
-Hey, Vivo.

46:50.766 --> 46:51.809
Are you scared?

46:52.643 --> 46:56.021
You know, my dad used to sing to me
when I was scared.

46:56.688 --> 46:57.773
So did Andrés.

46:57.856 --> 47:01.193
Hey! We could sing Marta's song.
That would cheer us up.

47:01.276 --> 47:03.278
[rapping] ♪ I am here
Just on another shore ♪

47:03.362 --> 47:05.072
♪ Always in your corner ♪

47:05.155 --> 47:06.281
♪ Watching you soar ♪

47:06.365 --> 47:08.075
[beatboxing poorly]

47:09.117 --> 47:11.036
-[imitating drums]
-[groans quietly]

47:11.119 --> 47:13.872
Drumming's in my blood.
I could teach you if you want.

47:13.956 --> 47:16.375
You're gonna teach me how to play drums?

47:17.042 --> 47:17.918
Here, Vivo.

47:18.001 --> 47:19.294
Check this out.

47:19.378 --> 47:21.797
-Try a simple beat.
-[drumming poorly]

47:21.880 --> 47:25.175
[chuckles]
That thing you're doing is noise. Observe.

47:25.259 --> 47:26.844
[drumming rhythmically]

47:30.389 --> 47:32.224
Wow. You learn quick.

47:32.307 --> 47:34.268
I must be a really good teacher.

47:34.351 --> 47:35.561
Uh-huh.

47:35.644 --> 47:36.687
Follow my lead, kid.

47:38.313 --> 47:41.567
-[plays drumroll]
-Whoa! This sounds good.

47:41.650 --> 47:43.944
Yeah, I see, uh, potential.

47:44.027 --> 47:45.362
Raw talent.

47:45.445 --> 47:46.989
[both drumming rhythmically]

47:47.072 --> 47:48.198
[Gabi laughs]

47:48.991 --> 47:50.075
Come on, Vivo.

47:50.158 --> 47:51.827
Let loose, grandpa.

47:51.910 --> 47:54.413
Grandpa? Could a grandpa do this?

47:54.496 --> 47:55.873
[drumbeat intensifies]

47:55.956 --> 47:56.874
[Gabi laughs]

47:56.957 --> 48:00.586
-Oh, yeah, Vivo.
-Woo-hoo!

48:00.669 --> 48:04.298
♪ Remember the size of the world before ♪

48:04.381 --> 48:09.386
[both] ♪ Now it's you and I
Just you and I ♪

48:09.469 --> 48:13.223
[Vivo] ♪ And now the horizon
Holds so much more ♪

48:13.307 --> 48:15.434
[both] ♪ And it's do or die ♪

48:15.517 --> 48:18.478
♪ Yeah, it's do or die ♪

48:18.562 --> 48:22.649
♪ All I can do when the road bends ♪

48:22.733 --> 48:27.279
-♪ We bounce to the beat of our own drum ♪
-♪ Is lean into the curve ♪

48:27.362 --> 48:31.617
♪ And all I can do
When the tank's run dry ♪

48:31.700 --> 48:36.038
-♪ We bounce to the beat of our own drum ♪
-♪ Is see what's in reserve ♪

48:36.121 --> 48:40.459
♪ And all I can do
When the plans break down ♪

48:40.542 --> 48:45.005
-♪ We wow in a world full of ho-hum ♪
-♪ Is stay on my feet ♪

48:45.088 --> 48:47.424
♪ And all I can do ♪

48:47.507 --> 48:49.843
♪ At the end of the day ♪

48:49.927 --> 48:52.804
♪ Is play on, play on ♪

48:53.347 --> 48:54.681
♪ And keep the beat ♪

48:54.765 --> 48:56.266
-[Gabi imitates drums]
-[sighs]

48:56.350 --> 48:58.060
Come on, you can't stop now.

48:58.143 --> 49:00.354
Let's keep the beat going, partner.

49:00.437 --> 49:03.065
[sighs] Not the beat. Not my partner.

49:03.148 --> 49:04.691
[thunder crashes]

49:05.275 --> 49:06.735
[birds cawing]

49:08.612 --> 49:09.446
[Vivo whimpers]

49:09.947 --> 49:12.616
Don't worry, Vivo.
It's just a little drizzle.

49:12.699 --> 49:15.035
-It'll probably blow over.
-[thunder crashes]

49:16.078 --> 49:18.121
[Gabi screams] Hold on tight, Vivo!

49:19.373 --> 49:21.375
Ah! Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

49:23.627 --> 49:24.461
Whoa!

49:24.962 --> 49:25.837
No!

49:26.880 --> 49:27.965
The song!

49:31.134 --> 49:33.595
-All right, Vivo, I'll get it.
-No, no, no. I got it.

49:34.221 --> 49:36.098
Vivo! Ah! I can't see.

49:37.641 --> 49:40.185
No, no, no, no
This can't be happening. [grunts]

49:41.395 --> 49:42.854
Yes! [screams]

49:42.938 --> 49:44.606
-Vivo!
-No!

49:44.690 --> 49:46.149
[Gabi] I got it!

49:46.233 --> 49:48.276
-The song?
-Don't worry, Vivo.

49:48.360 --> 49:50.821
I'll take care of it. I promise!

49:50.904 --> 49:51.863
Gabi!

49:52.572 --> 49:53.949
[panting]

49:57.744 --> 50:01.039
Okay, don't panic. You just lost the song.

50:01.123 --> 50:02.541
And it's with Gabi.

50:03.250 --> 50:06.670
What am I gonna do?
I just need a new plan.

50:06.753 --> 50:09.339
New plan. New plan.
New plan. New plan. New plan. I got it.

50:12.175 --> 50:14.136
Gabi!

50:14.219 --> 50:16.096
-[voice echoes]
-[thunder crashes]

50:16.179 --> 50:18.181
[Gabi's voice mail]
You have reached Gabi's robot.

50:18.265 --> 50:19.766
Leave a message. Beep.

50:19.850 --> 50:22.853
Gabriela Maria,
pick up your phone right now!

50:22.936 --> 50:24.938
I saw the bus schedule on your computer.

50:25.022 --> 50:27.065
If you think you're in trouble now,

50:27.149 --> 50:29.776
ooh, it's about to get worse.

50:31.778 --> 50:33.905
-[car horn beeps]
-[tires screech]

50:35.282 --> 50:38.702
I am right next to the bus, honking.
This is me.

50:38.785 --> 50:40.287
[imitating horn honking]

50:40.370 --> 50:41.830
I know you can hear me.

50:44.332 --> 50:45.709
[muffled] Pull over!

50:45.792 --> 50:47.711
-[bus driver] Huh? What the--
-Aah!

50:47.794 --> 50:51.339
Uh, you're not gonna
let her pass us, are you?

50:51.423 --> 50:52.966
Not on my watch.

50:53.050 --> 50:54.009
[passengers cheer]

50:55.886 --> 50:58.472
No, no, no, no, no.
Don't you drive away from me.

51:00.849 --> 51:02.976
-Gabi!
-[car horn beeping]

51:03.935 --> 51:05.103
[Vivo] Gabi!

51:05.812 --> 51:07.355
Gabi!

51:07.898 --> 51:09.357
Gabi!

51:09.441 --> 51:11.151
[wheezes]

51:11.234 --> 51:14.196
She's not responding.
I gotta start searching this swamp.

51:14.279 --> 51:15.781
[birds cawing]

51:15.864 --> 51:17.824
Birds. Bird's-eye view, perfect.

51:17.908 --> 51:21.244
Hey, you guys!
I need your help spotting somebody--

51:21.995 --> 51:23.163
[screams, grunts]

51:24.956 --> 51:25.791
[grunts]

51:28.418 --> 51:30.087
[yelps] Ugh.

51:31.379 --> 51:32.756
Oh, good. A bird.

51:32.839 --> 51:36.718
Excuse me. Uh, I'm Vivo.
I got separated from my friend.

51:36.802 --> 51:38.595
Purple hair, necktie. Ah!

51:39.596 --> 51:41.973
Ah. Could you maybe fly me up
and help me spot her?

51:42.057 --> 51:43.350
Normally, I'd help a guy out,

51:43.433 --> 51:47.354
but… [chuckles] …I'm gettin' ready
to take the long dirt nap.

51:47.437 --> 51:49.314
What? No, no, no, no, no, no!

51:49.397 --> 51:52.067
Don't talk like that!
I'm sure you have a lot to live for.

51:52.150 --> 51:55.779
[laughs] It's not like that.
Actually, I'm taking a literal nap.

51:55.862 --> 51:57.906
Yeah, I'm just hibernating

51:57.989 --> 51:59.991
until the end of my life.

52:00.075 --> 52:02.911
[laughs] I mean, the end of dating season.

52:02.994 --> 52:05.163
Dating. Sounds horrible. As I was saying--

52:05.247 --> 52:07.415
You don't understand, Vivo.
All my life I've been told,

52:07.499 --> 52:09.126
"Don't worry, Dancarino."

52:09.209 --> 52:10.210
"One dating season,

52:10.293 --> 52:13.130
you're gonna find the girl of your dreams,
and love's gonna pick you up."

52:13.213 --> 52:15.382
-That's great. But I got a thing. Huh?
-[birds chirping]

52:17.926 --> 52:23.515
♪ Love's gonna pick you up
And never put you down ♪

52:26.226 --> 52:29.938
Yeah. We all know the tune.
Wanna cool it with all that love? [scoffs]

52:30.021 --> 52:32.274
Um, so, I'm kind of
in a bit of a time crunch.

52:32.357 --> 52:35.902
I've been here for eight,
count them, eight straight seasons,

52:35.986 --> 52:38.989
and instead of love picking me up,
it's just dumped me in a ditch.

52:39.072 --> 52:40.157
Tragic. Anyway--

52:40.240 --> 52:43.451
I'm an invisible spoonbill.
No one cares I'm alive.

52:44.494 --> 52:46.246
Especially Valentina.

52:47.372 --> 52:51.668
[angelic choir vocalizing]

52:51.751 --> 52:54.129
-Valentina's looking at me, isn't she?
-Yeah.

52:54.212 --> 52:55.839
Nobody knows I know you.
You don't know me.

52:55.922 --> 52:59.467
-Good luck finding your friend. Bye!
-Ah! Wait. Get out of there.

52:59.551 --> 53:03.221
-Have you tried telling her how you feel?
-[gasps] No! I can't tell her.

53:03.305 --> 53:04.264
I'm scared.

53:05.640 --> 53:08.727
No, I've heard this song before.
It doesn't end well.

53:09.352 --> 53:12.439
Come on, I'll coach you through it.
Then you'll help me find my friend. Deal?

53:12.522 --> 53:14.900
[quaveringly] Okay, deal.

53:16.526 --> 53:18.528
Now, introduce yourself.

53:19.196 --> 53:21.031
Hi, you're Dancarino.

53:21.114 --> 53:23.283
I mean, I'm… [voice cracks] I'm Dancarino.

53:23.909 --> 53:26.870
Hmm. Enchanted.

53:26.953 --> 53:29.998
-[gasps] No. Back to my hole.
-No, no, no. Hey, hey, focus.

53:30.081 --> 53:32.459
Smile and compliment her.

53:32.542 --> 53:35.128
-Uh, Valentina. [inhales]
-You got this.

53:35.212 --> 53:39.049
Your eyes are like two huge pools--

53:39.132 --> 53:43.595
No, they're like
two big bayous in your face.

53:43.678 --> 53:46.431
Bayous? In my face?

53:46.514 --> 53:48.433
[groaning] Oh no.

53:48.516 --> 53:52.354
That's the nicest thing
anyone's ever said about my-- [screams]

53:53.271 --> 53:54.981
[gurgles, spits]

53:55.065 --> 53:56.441
[coughing]

53:57.567 --> 53:59.653
Got a frog in my throat.

54:02.155 --> 54:03.865
-[croaks]
-Sorry, Gary.

54:03.949 --> 54:04.783
[Gary scoffs]

54:05.242 --> 54:07.452
[chuckles, gasps]

54:08.370 --> 54:12.374
-Oh, they're perfect for each other.
-[hoarsely] Oh, Dancarino. [coughing]

54:12.457 --> 54:15.210
You have such handsome plumage.

54:15.293 --> 54:18.880
It's nice for my eye…
uh, bayous… [chuckles] …to look at.

54:18.964 --> 54:22.008
'Cause they're actually my eyes. [laughs]

54:22.092 --> 54:23.468
[laughs]

54:23.551 --> 54:25.345
This is going strangely well.

54:25.971 --> 54:28.306
Now, take her hand.

54:29.641 --> 54:31.226
-Ow!
-Oh, sorry. Oh!

54:31.309 --> 54:33.144
-I'm so sorry.
-No, no, no, it's fine.

54:33.228 --> 54:35.021
I have another eye. It's totally great.

54:35.105 --> 54:37.107
-[Valentina] Ow!
-Oh! Easy with the beak.

54:37.691 --> 54:40.068
Not too quick, Dan.
Uh, yeah. Go in at an angle.

54:40.151 --> 54:41.361
To the left. Yes.

54:41.861 --> 54:42.988
That's it.

54:43.071 --> 54:45.198
Now, fly away together.

54:45.282 --> 54:46.491
[both giggle]

54:47.158 --> 54:52.998
♪ Love's gonna pick you up
And never put you down ♪

54:53.623 --> 54:54.582
[Vivo] Perfect.

54:56.918 --> 54:59.671
What? Wait, you were supposed to help me.

54:59.754 --> 55:00.630
Come back!

55:00.714 --> 55:02.132
We had a deal.

55:02.215 --> 55:05.343
-We had a deal!
-[water splashes]

55:10.515 --> 55:13.560
-[Marta singing scales]
-Okay, vamos. Heads up, everyone.

55:13.643 --> 55:15.186
Showtime's in four hours.

55:15.270 --> 55:17.939
We need to get
the lighting cues down for the finale.

55:18.815 --> 55:21.818
Excuse me, mi niña. Any word from Andrés?

55:21.901 --> 55:24.738
Not yet, señora.
I'll double-check right away.

55:24.821 --> 55:25.780
Thank you.

55:28.700 --> 55:30.744
Where are you, my friend?

55:41.546 --> 55:43.548
[groaning]

55:45.175 --> 55:46.092
Vivo?

55:46.593 --> 55:49.346
Vivo? Where are you?

55:49.429 --> 55:50.305
[gasps]

55:50.388 --> 55:53.600
Oh no, where is it?
Where is it? Where's the song?

55:54.601 --> 55:57.437
Come on. Vivo's gonna kill me. [gasps]

55:57.520 --> 56:00.231
[foreboding music playing]

56:00.857 --> 56:02.567
Oh. Whoa!

56:02.650 --> 56:03.485
[groans]

56:06.863 --> 56:09.115
Ooh. It's just a turtle.

56:09.199 --> 56:11.076
-[Troop girl] It's not just a turtle.
-[screams]

56:13.328 --> 56:14.371
Becky?

56:14.454 --> 56:16.456
It's a Florida red-bellied cooter.

56:16.539 --> 56:18.750
It belongs here.
It's native to these parts.

56:18.833 --> 56:21.169
Unlike your friend. Where is he?

56:21.252 --> 56:23.880
Um, he's kinda missing.

56:23.963 --> 56:24.881
[gasps]

56:24.964 --> 56:28.885
You lost a kinkajou in the Everglades?

56:29.469 --> 56:32.180
Well, congratulations, Hernández.
You've killed him.

56:32.263 --> 56:33.306
Wait, what?

56:33.390 --> 56:36.142
A kinkajou
cannot survive in this environment.

56:36.226 --> 56:39.604
His natural predator
is every animal in here.

56:39.687 --> 56:43.316
He needs to be quarantined.
And you are gonna help us find him.

56:43.400 --> 56:45.777
Heh. I'm not helping you.

56:45.860 --> 56:49.197
-Then I guess you don't want this.
-[gasps]

56:49.280 --> 56:51.282
You were looking for this song,
weren't you?

56:52.117 --> 56:53.910
No, I don't care about that song.

56:53.993 --> 56:57.038
Fine. Then we should recycle it. Eva?

56:57.122 --> 56:58.832
[gulps] Huh?

56:58.915 --> 56:59.833
Eat it.

57:00.375 --> 57:01.584
Yeah, all right.

57:01.668 --> 57:03.044
[suspenseful music playing]

57:11.177 --> 57:12.178
Wait!

57:12.262 --> 57:13.847
Fine, you win.

57:13.930 --> 57:17.559
I'll wear the uniform. I'll sell cookies.
I will do whatever you want.

57:17.642 --> 57:19.602
Just give me the song back.

57:19.686 --> 57:20.979
You get the song

57:21.104 --> 57:23.982
when the kinkajou
is safely in our custody.

57:24.774 --> 57:26.067
Gabi!

57:26.151 --> 57:28.027
Where are you, Gabi? [screams]

57:28.903 --> 57:30.113
[groans]

57:30.196 --> 57:32.782
Disgusting! Who am I kidding?

57:32.866 --> 57:35.952
I'm not cut out for this. I'll be lucky
to get out of this swamp alive.

57:36.035 --> 57:37.620
-Gabi!
-Shh.

57:39.330 --> 57:40.874
Did you just shush me?

57:40.957 --> 57:43.543
Buddy, be quiet.

57:44.043 --> 57:46.796
Seriously?
Do you have any idea what I've bee--

57:46.880 --> 57:48.465
Bup-bup-bup-bup-bup-bup-bup.

57:49.716 --> 57:52.886
Are you bup-bup-bup-bup-
bup-bup-bup-bup-bup-ing me?

57:52.969 --> 57:55.263
That's it. You want me to be quiet?

57:55.346 --> 57:57.849
[shouting] I'm being quiet!

57:57.932 --> 58:00.727
Yeah. I thought so. Walk away, buddy.

58:00.810 --> 58:04.522
We're in the middle of a swamp.
Who cares about a little noise?

58:04.606 --> 58:05.440
[chokes]

58:06.441 --> 58:08.026
Me.

58:08.109 --> 58:09.319
[screams]

58:10.278 --> 58:13.990
Mmm, what a lovely voice you have.

58:14.073 --> 58:16.367
Never seen you around these parts.

58:16.993 --> 58:19.579
My name's Lutador. You got a name?

58:19.662 --> 58:21.789
It's Vivo.

58:21.873 --> 58:24.709
Oh! My goodness, I hate that name.

58:24.792 --> 58:27.837
Your new name is Noisy.

58:27.921 --> 58:30.673
Noisy the Singing Rat. [chuckles]

58:30.757 --> 58:32.300
Yeah. [laughs nervously]

58:32.383 --> 58:33.968
I'm not a rat.

58:34.052 --> 58:36.179
What… what are you? A gibbon?

58:36.262 --> 58:38.056
I'm a kinkajou.

58:38.556 --> 58:42.143
Mmm. Sounds exotic. Hoo.

58:42.769 --> 58:45.230
Well, you listen right here,
little kinkajou.

58:46.105 --> 58:48.983
I hate noise.

58:49.567 --> 58:51.110
So you must be quiet.

58:51.653 --> 58:53.780
That's my rule, man.

58:53.863 --> 58:58.284
And everyone around these parts
understands it. Don't y'all?

58:59.035 --> 59:00.203
[all sucking in breath]

59:02.455 --> 59:03.289
[taps softly]

59:03.373 --> 59:06.042
[both squeaking quietly]

59:08.878 --> 59:11.923
Mmm. That's what I like to hear.

59:12.006 --> 59:15.468
Absolutely nothing.

59:15.552 --> 59:18.179
Uh, I'm sorry. I promise,
you won't hear a peep from me.

59:18.263 --> 59:20.598
You want quiet?
I can do quiet. I'll be quiet.

59:20.682 --> 59:24.018
[chuckles]
I know very well you're gonna be quiet.

59:24.561 --> 59:26.896
Deathly silent, in fact.

59:26.980 --> 59:28.982
All my meals are.

59:29.065 --> 59:29.899
[Vivo] Whoa!

59:30.525 --> 59:31.568
[grunting]

59:32.235 --> 59:35.363
Ho ho ho ho! Would you look at that?

59:35.446 --> 59:37.407
Oh, my friend…

59:37.490 --> 59:41.077
[in singsong]
…you're about to run out of tree.

59:45.164 --> 59:47.542
[Vivo screaming]

59:52.547 --> 59:55.341
Huh? [screaming]

59:56.593 --> 59:59.178
Oh, thank goodness. I'm saved.

59:59.262 --> 1:00:00.555
Are you an angel?

1:00:01.055 --> 1:00:03.057
[muffled] Vivo, it's me!

1:00:03.141 --> 1:00:05.852
Dancarino? You saved me? Whoa!

1:00:05.935 --> 1:00:09.063
♪ Yes, I saved you
'Cause love saved me ♪

1:00:09.147 --> 1:00:11.357
-What?
-♪ Vivo, when you found me ♪

1:00:11.441 --> 1:00:13.192
-♪ I was low as I could be ♪
-♪ High up! ♪

1:00:13.276 --> 1:00:15.028
-♪ You picked me up ♪
-[Valentina] ♪ So high ♪

1:00:15.111 --> 1:00:18.072
♪ And you changed my whole demeanor
Like a perfect ballerina ♪

1:00:18.156 --> 1:00:20.533
-♪ Yes, I found my Valentina ♪
-That's me!

1:00:20.617 --> 1:00:24.162
♪ I told Valentina
About the mission you were on for love ♪

1:00:24.245 --> 1:00:25.538
♪ You poor little honey bear ♪

1:00:25.622 --> 1:00:27.790
♪ So tired of running
We're going to get you there ♪

1:00:27.874 --> 1:00:31.169
♪ And sweet Valentina said
Let's help him from above ♪

1:00:31.252 --> 1:00:34.505
♪ So we thought we'd swing by you
Come and help you with a bird's-eye view ♪

1:00:34.589 --> 1:00:38.843
♪ Love's gonna pick you up
And never put you down ♪

1:00:38.926 --> 1:00:41.554
♪ Cool, please stop singing
We're miles away from the ground ♪

1:00:41.638 --> 1:00:45.350
♪ Love's gonna kick your butt
And drag you around ♪

1:00:45.433 --> 1:00:48.728
♪ Let's help your friend
Then you and me fly south ♪

1:00:48.811 --> 1:00:52.732
♪ You take that road
To deliver that love you found ♪

1:00:52.815 --> 1:00:55.485
♪ Where we're going
We don't need roads, we don't need roads ♪

1:00:55.568 --> 1:01:00.948
♪ That one set of footprints
Was love dragging you around ♪

1:01:01.032 --> 1:01:02.909
♪ Dragging you around, yeah ♪

1:01:03.534 --> 1:01:04.911
Oh, you're gonna help me?

1:01:04.994 --> 1:01:06.412
-Mm-hmm.
-Thank you.

1:01:06.496 --> 1:01:08.498
Don't worry that little head of yours.

1:01:08.581 --> 1:01:10.541
I promise, we will find your friend.

1:01:10.625 --> 1:01:14.087
[Dancarino]
Aw, that's right, my little twirly birdy.

1:01:14.170 --> 1:01:16.214
-[Valentina] My tweety sweetie.
-[Vivo] Okay.

1:01:16.297 --> 1:01:18.675
-[Dancarino] My little cheeky beaky.
-[Vivo] Um…

1:01:18.758 --> 1:01:21.052
[Valentina] My dapper flapper.

1:01:21.135 --> 1:01:24.013
Okay! Less lovebird, more bird's-eye!

1:01:24.097 --> 1:01:27.684
♪ Love's gonna pick you up
And never put you down ♪

1:01:27.767 --> 1:01:31.062
♪ I said love's gonna kick your butt
And drag you around, yeah ♪

1:01:31.938 --> 1:01:33.314
Vivo!

1:01:34.607 --> 1:01:35.983
Vivo!

1:01:36.067 --> 1:01:38.277
Come on, Vivo!

1:01:38.361 --> 1:01:41.155
See? I told you. He's not coming.

1:01:41.239 --> 1:01:43.241
Becky, just give me back the song.

1:01:43.324 --> 1:01:46.452
No kinkajou, no song. Yell louder.

1:01:46.536 --> 1:01:49.288
Ugh. Fine. Vivo!

1:01:49.372 --> 1:01:51.708
Vivo, where are you?

1:01:51.791 --> 1:01:53.418
-[grass rustling]
-Vivo?

1:01:54.085 --> 1:01:57.839
Vivo, stay there.
The Sand Dollars are right behind me.

1:01:57.922 --> 1:02:00.842
They have the song.
But don't worry, I have a plan.

1:02:00.925 --> 1:02:03.886
-[grass rustles]
-Stay there. Don't move.

1:02:05.054 --> 1:02:05.972
[hisses]

1:02:06.055 --> 1:02:07.223
[screaming]

1:02:10.935 --> 1:02:12.645
Snake!

1:02:13.187 --> 1:02:15.690
-[Troop girls gasp, scream]
-[Gabi] To the boat!

1:02:15.773 --> 1:02:17.066
[all panting]

1:02:17.692 --> 1:02:19.944
-[Gabi] Whoa!
-[Troop girls screaming]

1:02:21.821 --> 1:02:23.239
-[Gabi] Run! Run! Run!
-[Becky] Go!

1:02:24.824 --> 1:02:26.451
[Troop girl] He's right behind us!

1:02:26.951 --> 1:02:28.077
[Gabi grunting]

1:02:28.161 --> 1:02:29.328
[Eva] Faster!

1:02:30.246 --> 1:02:31.581
[shouts, grunts]

1:02:32.290 --> 1:02:33.791
Uh, this way! Whoa!

1:02:37.712 --> 1:02:39.213
[panting]

1:02:39.297 --> 1:02:41.007
Okay, I think we're safe here.

1:02:41.507 --> 1:02:42.550
[all scream]

1:02:42.633 --> 1:02:43.676
I guess I was wrong.

1:02:44.761 --> 1:02:45.720
[girls whimpering]

1:02:52.977 --> 1:02:54.896
[Troop girl] Oh no, he's gonna kill us!

1:02:57.315 --> 1:02:58.483
[Gabi] Let him have it!

1:02:59.108 --> 1:03:01.527
-[Eva] Get away!
-[Becky] Get back!

1:03:02.695 --> 1:03:06.365
-What else do you have in there?
-Ha! Eat string, snake!

1:03:08.743 --> 1:03:10.536
[Gabi chuckles sheepishly, grunts]

1:03:12.455 --> 1:03:13.790
[Lutador hisses]

1:03:13.873 --> 1:03:15.458
[girls screaming]

1:03:16.083 --> 1:03:18.127
Hey, wait. Did you hear that?

1:03:18.211 --> 1:03:20.004
That's Gabi. She's in trouble.

1:03:24.509 --> 1:03:26.177
[screaming continues]

1:03:28.346 --> 1:03:29.555
[Vivo] Hey, Lutador!

1:03:29.639 --> 1:03:31.933
-[drumming on tree]
-Leave them alone.

1:03:32.016 --> 1:03:33.976
[chuckles]

1:03:34.060 --> 1:03:36.854
If it ain't Noisy the Singing Rat.

1:03:36.938 --> 1:03:40.107
That's right. And noisier than ever.
Bop bop bop bop!

1:03:40.191 --> 1:03:42.443
Stop making the noise.

1:03:42.527 --> 1:03:43.694
Yeah? Come make me.

1:03:43.778 --> 1:03:45.696
With pleasure.

1:03:46.697 --> 1:03:49.325
Excuse me, ladies. I'll be right back.

1:03:50.326 --> 1:03:51.953
Vivo, what are you doing?

1:03:52.036 --> 1:03:54.413
I don't know.
But sometimes you gotta improvise.

1:03:54.497 --> 1:03:55.331
[both shout]

1:03:56.833 --> 1:03:58.000
-[thuds]
-[Vivo screams]

1:04:01.671 --> 1:04:03.714
-You got this, Vivo.
-Gabi.

1:04:03.798 --> 1:04:05.758
A kinkajou can't beat a python.

1:04:06.259 --> 1:04:08.052
[Lutador laughs menacingly]

1:04:08.135 --> 1:04:10.304
You still running up trees, Noisy?

1:04:10.388 --> 1:04:12.557
You rats never learn, do you?

1:04:12.640 --> 1:04:15.309
Don't just stand there, schmoopie.
Dig us a hole to hide in.

1:04:15.393 --> 1:04:16.519
I love you, baby!

1:04:18.688 --> 1:04:19.772
[Vivo] Oh no!

1:04:20.690 --> 1:04:22.316
[screaming]

1:04:22.400 --> 1:04:23.568
Vivo, watch out!

1:04:24.235 --> 1:04:25.862
[both grunting]

1:04:28.072 --> 1:04:29.532
[chomping]

1:04:29.615 --> 1:04:32.535
That's it. Okay.
Enough is enough. [grunts]

1:04:32.618 --> 1:04:34.996
-Huh.
-You can't run forever!

1:04:35.580 --> 1:04:38.583
Sure, I can.
Back in Havana, I do five shows a day.

1:04:39.083 --> 1:04:41.586
♪ Whoo! Tough crowd
Nothing I haven't seen before ♪

1:04:41.669 --> 1:04:44.213
♪ I'll have to pull out the stops
And give 'em even more ♪

1:04:44.297 --> 1:04:46.507
♪ It's tough to play
When you're prey facing a predator ♪

1:04:46.591 --> 1:04:48.634
♪ No time to pray
Find a way to slay your competitor ♪

1:04:48.718 --> 1:04:51.095
♪ Turn up the volume
When they would have you be quiet ♪

1:04:51.178 --> 1:04:53.180
♪ You turn up the rhythm
So they can never deny it ♪

1:04:53.264 --> 1:04:55.808
♪ You bounce when it counts
And give as good as you got ♪

1:04:55.892 --> 1:04:59.145
♪ 'Cause you're not gonna stop
Till they drop and you got 'em in a knot ♪

1:04:59.645 --> 1:05:01.898
[grunting] Get me out of here.

1:05:01.981 --> 1:05:03.399
-[groans]
-[Troop girl] Woo-hoo!

1:05:03.482 --> 1:05:05.610
-Yay! Good job, Vivo!
-[Gabi] Oh yeah!

1:05:05.693 --> 1:05:07.904
-[girls cheering]
-[gasps] Wait. Did we win?

1:05:08.404 --> 1:05:10.239
Gabi, are… are you okay?

1:05:11.574 --> 1:05:14.243
-You totally took down that snake!
-[Vivo chitters]

1:05:14.327 --> 1:05:17.496
-You are one crazy kinkajou.
-He's a hero.

1:05:17.580 --> 1:05:19.290
A fuzzy hero.

1:05:19.373 --> 1:05:21.667
I was wrong about you, Vivo.

1:05:21.751 --> 1:05:24.462
[clears throat] I mean, I still think
you really should be quarantined

1:05:24.545 --> 1:05:25.630
for ten days,

1:05:26.297 --> 1:05:30.134
but you did save us from an apex predator.

1:05:30.217 --> 1:05:33.304
So, I'm gonna let this one slide.

1:05:35.014 --> 1:05:37.350
So, we cool, right?

1:05:37.433 --> 1:05:38.976
Yeah, we're cool.

1:05:39.060 --> 1:05:41.896
Can we have the song back?

1:05:41.979 --> 1:05:43.272
Of course, the song.

1:05:43.773 --> 1:05:46.150
Wait, what? I ju… I just had it.

1:05:46.233 --> 1:05:47.568
Where did it go?

1:05:47.652 --> 1:05:48.611
[gasps]

1:05:49.654 --> 1:05:51.948
[somber music playing]

1:05:53.991 --> 1:05:54.951
Oh no.

1:06:03.125 --> 1:06:04.001
Andrés.

1:06:16.055 --> 1:06:19.016
[Marta hums]

1:06:19.100 --> 1:06:20.893
-[knocking at door]
-Come in.

1:06:21.894 --> 1:06:24.146
Is he… is he here?

1:06:25.398 --> 1:06:26.482
[woman] Oh, señora.

1:06:27.149 --> 1:06:28.818
I'm so sorry.

1:06:28.901 --> 1:06:32.697
ANDRÉS HERNÁNDEZ
A BELOVED MUSICIAN DIES IN LA HAVANA

1:06:33.698 --> 1:06:34.532
[gasps softly]

1:06:34.615 --> 1:06:36.492
[melancholy guitar music playing]

1:06:55.386 --> 1:06:59.181
♪ You spent your life making music ♪

1:07:01.225 --> 1:07:04.061
♪ I thought the song would never end ♪

1:07:06.605 --> 1:07:09.150
♪ Now it's so quiet ♪

1:07:12.528 --> 1:07:16.657
♪ All I wanna do
Is play again with you, my friend ♪

1:07:21.620 --> 1:07:22.455
[exhales deeply]

1:07:25.708 --> 1:07:27.376
Sorry again about the song.

1:07:28.586 --> 1:07:29.545
Thanks, Dan.

1:07:30.671 --> 1:07:33.966
So, um, what are you gonna do now?

1:07:35.009 --> 1:07:35.843
[sighs]

1:07:36.427 --> 1:07:38.262
Make my way back to Cuba, I guess.

1:07:39.513 --> 1:07:42.975
Without the song,
there's nothing left. I failed.

1:07:43.059 --> 1:07:47.104
Hey, hey, no! Don't say that.
You did all you could do.

1:07:47.188 --> 1:07:50.983
Dan, you don't understand.
Andrés gave me everything.

1:07:51.734 --> 1:07:53.861
And when he needed me, I turned my back.

1:07:54.361 --> 1:07:56.530
This was my one chance
to make things right.

1:07:57.865 --> 1:07:59.283
And I've let him down.

1:07:59.784 --> 1:08:03.996
♪ When the plane lands on the runway ♪

1:08:04.080 --> 1:08:07.958
♪ Keep this song inside your heart, ooh ♪

1:08:08.042 --> 1:08:09.710
Is that your uncle's song?

1:08:10.211 --> 1:08:11.879
[sighs] Yeah.

1:08:12.880 --> 1:08:16.258
-♪ When the years pass… ♪
-Oh no. She's at it again.

1:08:17.760 --> 1:08:20.846
She's butchering his song.
It's a musical massacre.

1:08:20.930 --> 1:08:24.850
[Gabi] ♪ I will be with you
When this song plays… ♪

1:08:24.934 --> 1:08:27.853
Just stop and listen to the melody.

1:08:28.395 --> 1:08:30.356
[recorder playing melody]

1:08:32.691 --> 1:08:33.567
[gasps]

1:08:38.239 --> 1:08:40.116
Hear? It's beautiful, right?

1:08:40.199 --> 1:08:41.742
Those are musical notes,

1:08:41.826 --> 1:08:45.412
written in a specific order
that people find pleasing to the ear.

1:08:45.496 --> 1:08:47.748
Those who know music call it a melody.

1:08:47.832 --> 1:08:49.416
[chittering]

1:08:49.500 --> 1:08:51.418
Vivo, you know the melody.

1:08:51.502 --> 1:08:53.921
Of course I do!
It's the foundation of music!

1:08:54.004 --> 1:08:55.381
And while you may know the lyrics,

1:08:55.464 --> 1:08:58.217
you have to learn the melody
in order to sing, because--

1:08:58.759 --> 1:09:02.221
Wait. You know the lyrics.
And I know the melody!

1:09:02.304 --> 1:09:04.348
Hey, you guys, Vivo knows the melody!

1:09:04.431 --> 1:09:06.267
-She knows the lyrics.
-This means…

1:09:06.350 --> 1:09:07.893
We've still got the song!

1:09:07.977 --> 1:09:10.062
The mission for love is back on!

1:09:10.980 --> 1:09:13.274
Turn the boat around.
We're going to Miami!

1:09:13.357 --> 1:09:14.567
What?

1:09:14.650 --> 1:09:16.068
[chittering]

1:09:17.027 --> 1:09:19.572
You heard the kinkajou.
Turn the boat around.

1:09:20.614 --> 1:09:22.283
[triumphant music playing]

1:09:27.955 --> 1:09:30.624
Huh. We got a second chance.

1:09:31.375 --> 1:09:33.002
Here, Vivo. Check this out.

1:09:35.087 --> 1:09:37.173
[notes playing]

1:09:39.425 --> 1:09:42.178
You play the keyboard,
and I'll write down the notes.

1:09:42.261 --> 1:09:43.762
[chittering]

1:09:43.846 --> 1:09:47.016
[melody playing on keyboard]

1:09:52.479 --> 1:09:54.440
"Your plane leaves in the morning."

1:09:54.523 --> 1:09:56.734
"Soon the world will see you shine."

1:09:56.817 --> 1:09:57.651
[chirps]

1:09:57.735 --> 1:10:00.154
[melody continues on keyboard]

1:10:03.949 --> 1:10:06.493
[melody playing rapidly]

1:10:10.706 --> 1:10:11.790
[chitters]

1:10:11.874 --> 1:10:15.419
Yeah, can you play that,
like, a hundred times slower?

1:10:15.502 --> 1:10:16.712
[chirps]

1:10:16.795 --> 1:10:19.048
[melody playing slowly]

1:10:25.346 --> 1:10:29.558
♪ All along inside your heart ♪

1:10:29.642 --> 1:10:32.478
♪ Oh, ooh ♪

1:10:32.978 --> 1:10:36.023
It's done.
Now we just have to get this to Marta.

1:10:36.106 --> 1:10:38.817
-[chirps]
-Ooh, one last thing.

1:10:44.073 --> 1:10:45.699
-Ooh!
-Oh yeah!

1:10:46.659 --> 1:10:48.410
-[chuckles]
-[Eva] Guys, look.

1:10:48.869 --> 1:10:50.913
I think I can see Miami.

1:10:50.996 --> 1:10:52.998
[upbeat music playing]

1:10:54.667 --> 1:10:58.045
Oh no. We're never gonna make it in time.

1:10:58.128 --> 1:11:00.214
Not without breaking a few rules.

1:11:00.297 --> 1:11:02.049
[engine revs]

1:11:02.132 --> 1:11:04.802
[Becky] Hold on to your cookies!

1:11:09.265 --> 1:11:12.685
♪ Survived another disaster
Does this thing go any faster? ♪

1:11:12.768 --> 1:11:16.397
♪ We're out of time
The sun is going down ♪

1:11:16.480 --> 1:11:19.900
♪ When I thought we were done for
My new friend gave us an encore ♪

1:11:19.984 --> 1:11:22.861
♪ Let's reach the shore
Of this Miami town ♪

1:11:22.945 --> 1:11:26.198
[Gabi and Vivo]
♪ Remember the size of the world before ♪

1:11:26.282 --> 1:11:30.202
♪ It was you and I, just you and I ♪

1:11:30.286 --> 1:11:33.330
♪ And now the horizon holds so much more ♪

1:11:33.414 --> 1:11:37.084
♪ And it's do or die
Yeah, it's do or die ♪

1:11:37.668 --> 1:11:41.046
[electronic vocals]
♪ M-I-A-M-I, running out of time ♪

1:11:41.130 --> 1:11:44.341
Ms. Sandoval,
this is your half-hour call.

1:11:44.925 --> 1:11:48.262
♪ M-I-A-M-I, running out of time ♪

1:11:48.345 --> 1:11:52.057
[Marta in Spanish] ♪ We need more time ♪

1:11:52.141 --> 1:11:55.144
♪ M-I-A-M-I
Running out of time ♪

1:11:55.227 --> 1:11:59.189
-♪ We gotta go, we gotta go, we gotta go ♪
-[Vivo] ♪ I know, I know, I know ♪

1:11:59.273 --> 1:12:01.984
♪ M-I-A-M-I
Running out of time ♪

1:12:02.067 --> 1:12:03.527
[Vivo] ♪ Turn up the tempo ♪

1:12:03.610 --> 1:12:06.196
[Gabi] ♪ Turn up the tempo ♪

1:12:06.280 --> 1:12:09.283
[Rosa] ♪ Her name is Gabi
She's ten, she's my daughter ♪

1:12:09.366 --> 1:12:13.037
♪ I know she was on this bus
She bought this ticket ♪

1:12:13.120 --> 1:12:15.664
♪ Hey, listen, lady
It's been a long day ♪

1:12:15.748 --> 1:12:18.500
♪ Like I said, she was not with us ♪

1:12:18.584 --> 1:12:19.835
I need a nap.

1:12:25.132 --> 1:12:26.383
[gasps]

1:12:26.467 --> 1:12:29.011
♪ We'll get there in time
And do so much more ♪

1:12:29.094 --> 1:12:32.973
♪ 'Cause it's you and I, just you and I ♪

1:12:33.057 --> 1:12:35.893
♪ We'll run, and we'll climb
Till we reach her door ♪

1:12:35.976 --> 1:12:39.855
♪ 'Cause it's do or die
Yeah, it's do or die ♪

1:12:40.898 --> 1:12:41.815
Ticket, please.

1:12:41.899 --> 1:12:43.984
Uh, no hablo inglés.

1:12:44.068 --> 1:12:47.613
Ah, no te preocupes.
Hablo español perfectamente.

1:12:47.696 --> 1:12:50.074
[chuckles nervously] ¡Excelente!

1:12:50.157 --> 1:12:53.744
Gabriela!
You stay right where you are, señorita.

1:12:53.827 --> 1:12:55.537
-Oh no, it's Mom.
-Hey.

1:12:55.621 --> 1:12:58.207
-Creí que no hablabas inglés. Hey!
-[Gabi] Adiós!

1:12:58.290 --> 1:13:00.084
-[Rosa] Gabi!
-Security to the entrance.

1:13:00.167 --> 1:13:03.212
♪ M-I-A-M-I
Running out of time ♪

1:13:03.295 --> 1:13:06.340
Ms. Sandoval,
this is your five-minute call.

1:13:06.423 --> 1:13:08.967
♪ M-I-A-M-I
Running out of time ♪

1:13:09.051 --> 1:13:10.552
[grunts, squeals]

1:13:10.636 --> 1:13:11.804
Hey, let go!

1:13:11.887 --> 1:13:12.805
Gotcha.

1:13:12.888 --> 1:13:15.682
-[gasps, growls]
-[security guard yelps]

1:13:15.766 --> 1:13:19.395
-♪ Let's go, let's go, let's go ♪
-♪ I know, I know, I know, I know ♪

1:13:19.478 --> 1:13:21.897
♪ M-I-A-M-I
Running out of time ♪

1:13:21.980 --> 1:13:23.190
♪ It's not too late ♪

1:13:23.273 --> 1:13:25.567
♪ We're almost there
There's nothing left to do but climb ♪

1:13:25.651 --> 1:13:28.362
♪ M-I-A-M-I
Running out of time ♪

1:13:28.445 --> 1:13:31.365
[both] ♪ We're out of time ♪

1:13:31.949 --> 1:13:34.701
[Gabi grunting]

1:13:35.953 --> 1:13:40.040
[gasps] Up there, Vivo. Climb through
and unlock the door from the other side.

1:13:41.625 --> 1:13:42.918
[yelps, grunts]

1:13:44.878 --> 1:13:45.963
Oh no.

1:13:49.299 --> 1:13:51.135
-Vivo, hurry. They're coming.
-[doors opening]

1:13:51.218 --> 1:13:52.761
[Vivo exerting]

1:13:53.554 --> 1:13:54.638
[Gabi exerting]

1:13:54.721 --> 1:13:55.889
It's not opening.

1:13:55.973 --> 1:13:57.182
What's wrong?

1:13:58.058 --> 1:14:00.727
-[guard 1] She's not down here.
-[guard 2] She must be this way.

1:14:01.603 --> 1:14:04.273
[exhales] Okay, Vivo, one last plan.

1:14:05.274 --> 1:14:06.358
[chirps]

1:14:06.442 --> 1:14:08.318
[Gabi] You have to go without me.

1:14:08.402 --> 1:14:09.695
[whimpers]

1:14:09.778 --> 1:14:11.238
[Gabi] It's okay, it's okay.

1:14:11.738 --> 1:14:13.740
Here, take this.

1:14:14.700 --> 1:14:17.369
So you… you won't forget me.

1:14:19.621 --> 1:14:20.456
[chitters sadly]

1:14:20.539 --> 1:14:22.749
[Gabi] Vivo,
you have to finish the mission.

1:14:23.250 --> 1:14:24.751
For the both of us.

1:14:26.420 --> 1:14:27.546
All right, partner.

1:14:33.594 --> 1:14:35.804
[suspenseful music playing]

1:14:36.555 --> 1:14:37.806
[guard 2] We got her.

1:14:40.893 --> 1:14:42.895
Hi, Mom. [chuckles nervously]

1:14:44.354 --> 1:14:47.649
I understand,
but Marta is taking this really hard.

1:14:47.733 --> 1:14:49.401
Yes, she says she can't go on.

1:14:49.902 --> 1:14:52.404
-Look, I'll check back in five minutes.
-[gasps]

1:14:52.905 --> 1:14:54.364
[footsteps receding]

1:14:59.453 --> 1:15:00.287
Marta?

1:15:00.370 --> 1:15:02.206
[Marta crying softly]

1:15:06.627 --> 1:15:07.461
Hmm.

1:15:19.723 --> 1:15:20.766
Andrés.

1:15:22.643 --> 1:15:23.477
[gasps]

1:15:24.311 --> 1:15:25.145
[chitters]

1:15:31.026 --> 1:15:32.027
[chirps]

1:15:32.945 --> 1:15:35.239
Are you Vivo?

1:15:35.822 --> 1:15:36.865
[chitters]

1:15:38.200 --> 1:15:40.786
You came all the way from Cuba?

1:15:41.578 --> 1:15:43.121
What are you doing here?

1:15:49.628 --> 1:15:50.462
[gasps]

1:15:50.963 --> 1:15:52.047
"Para Marta."

1:15:54.675 --> 1:15:56.134
Andrés wrote this.

1:15:56.927 --> 1:15:58.178
For me?

1:15:58.262 --> 1:15:59.429
[chirps]

1:16:00.806 --> 1:16:02.307
[weeping softly]

1:16:05.435 --> 1:16:06.270
[chitters]

1:16:07.229 --> 1:16:08.480
[Marta] Thank you.

1:16:09.815 --> 1:16:12.651
He never told me he felt this way.

1:16:15.153 --> 1:16:16.905
I love you too, Andrés.

1:16:19.658 --> 1:16:22.244
-Oh, Vivo, thank you.
-[Vivo coos]

1:16:23.078 --> 1:16:24.496
-[knocking on door]
-[woman] Señora?

1:16:24.580 --> 1:16:26.373
We're ready whenever you are.

1:16:27.708 --> 1:16:28.792
I have to go.

1:16:29.376 --> 1:16:30.460
[chuckles softly]

1:16:30.544 --> 1:16:35.132
And here I thought this concert
was about saying goodbye to the old songs,

1:16:35.215 --> 1:16:38.552
but now, I have a new song to sing.

1:16:42.306 --> 1:16:43.557
You know, Vivo,

1:16:44.182 --> 1:16:46.393
Andrés would be so proud of you.

1:16:46.476 --> 1:16:47.603
Mwah.

1:16:52.357 --> 1:16:53.191
[sighs]

1:16:56.653 --> 1:16:59.031
[gentle piano music playing]

1:17:19.593 --> 1:17:20.594
[car horns honking]

1:17:26.058 --> 1:17:29.936
But, Mom, Vivo needed to deliver
a love song to Marta.

1:17:30.062 --> 1:17:33.065
Do you hear yourself?
Gabriela, this is crazy!

1:17:33.148 --> 1:17:36.526
You see? This is why I didn't tell you.
I knew you wouldn't get it.

1:17:36.610 --> 1:17:38.862
Oh, ho ho ho ho, I get you all right.

1:17:38.945 --> 1:17:41.156
No. No, you don't.

1:17:41.239 --> 1:17:42.699
Not like Dad did.

1:17:42.783 --> 1:17:45.118
No, no, no.
You're not doing that, Gabriela.

1:17:45.202 --> 1:17:46.995
He's not here. I'm here.

1:17:47.079 --> 1:17:49.915
And I know, I know I'm not your father.

1:17:49.998 --> 1:17:52.626
I know I'm not funny,
and I don't do music.

1:17:52.709 --> 1:17:55.462
[inhales shakily]
But you can talk to me.

1:17:55.545 --> 1:17:58.256
You don't even understand
why this is important to me.

1:18:00.300 --> 1:18:02.052
Only Vivo does.

1:18:02.135 --> 1:18:03.553
Vivo is in Cuba.

1:18:04.471 --> 1:18:06.765
-[screams]
-[screams]

1:18:06.848 --> 1:18:07.808
Vivo!

1:18:09.017 --> 1:18:10.018
[chittering]

1:18:19.027 --> 1:18:20.821
Did you get the song to Marta?

1:18:21.321 --> 1:18:22.155
[chirps]

1:18:22.656 --> 1:18:23.573
You did it.

1:18:24.199 --> 1:18:25.409
[coos]

1:18:26.118 --> 1:18:28.203
That's right. We did it.

1:18:28.745 --> 1:18:29.705
[Rosa gasps softly]

1:18:30.372 --> 1:18:32.374
Wait. Wait. Wait.

1:18:32.999 --> 1:18:34.793
You were telling me the truth?

1:18:36.586 --> 1:18:37.838
Oh, Gabi. [exhales]

1:18:39.131 --> 1:18:40.006
But still,

1:18:40.632 --> 1:18:44.094
you can't just go a hundred miles
to Miami without telling me.

1:18:44.177 --> 1:18:46.763
I know. I'm sorry, okay?

1:18:46.847 --> 1:18:50.434
But I j… I just had to deliver tío's song.

1:18:51.226 --> 1:18:54.896
[crying] He… he didn't get to tell
Marta he loved her.

1:18:56.898 --> 1:18:57.816
Just like

1:18:59.443 --> 1:19:01.153
I never got to tell Dad how…

1:19:02.112 --> 1:19:03.613
how much I loved him.

1:19:04.906 --> 1:19:07.325
[sniffling, crying]

1:19:09.327 --> 1:19:10.245
[car door opens]

1:19:13.248 --> 1:19:14.082
[sobbing softly]

1:19:21.131 --> 1:19:26.178
Your dad knew you loved him
every moment from when he first met you.

1:19:26.261 --> 1:19:27.929
And that love, Gabriela,

1:19:28.638 --> 1:19:31.558
that love lives forever in your heart.

1:19:32.058 --> 1:19:33.185
[cries softly]

1:19:35.353 --> 1:19:36.563
[chirps]

1:19:39.775 --> 1:19:41.860
[in Spanish] Welcome to the family, Vivo.

1:19:41.943 --> 1:19:44.613
[Vivo coos]

1:19:45.405 --> 1:19:46.448
All right.

1:19:46.531 --> 1:19:49.868
You two better buckle up,
'cause we got a concert to get to.

1:19:50.744 --> 1:19:52.829
-[mambo music plays]
-[car tires screech]

1:19:52.913 --> 1:19:54.581
[Marta in Spanish] ♪ Say present ♪

1:19:54.664 --> 1:19:56.416
♪ Say present ♪

1:19:56.500 --> 1:20:01.046
♪ Past, future, yesterday, and tomorrow
Say present ♪

1:20:01.630 --> 1:20:05.550
♪ What is mine, what is yours
Miami, La Havana, say present ♪

1:20:08.178 --> 1:20:09.888
♪ Long live to my people! ♪

1:20:09.971 --> 1:20:12.849
[audience cheering]

1:20:14.392 --> 1:20:17.187
Gracias, everyone. Thank you.

1:20:18.021 --> 1:20:20.190
And to say farewell,

1:20:20.857 --> 1:20:22.984
I'd like to finish with a song.

1:20:23.068 --> 1:20:25.946
A song written by an old friend

1:20:27.572 --> 1:20:30.659
and delivered with the help of new ones.

1:20:31.159 --> 1:20:32.994
-[Vivo and Gabi gasp]
-[Gabi giggles]

1:20:41.753 --> 1:20:44.464
♪ Mambo Cabana, oh ♪

1:20:45.924 --> 1:20:49.928
♪ Mambo Cabana, oh ♪

1:20:50.011 --> 1:20:52.889
♪ Your plane leaves in the morning ♪

1:20:54.307 --> 1:20:57.310
♪ Soon the world will see you shine ♪

1:20:58.645 --> 1:21:00.939
♪ And I wish I could go with you ♪

1:21:02.899 --> 1:21:05.485
